Commentary.Commentary: We are back for West Indies' first innings! The Bangladeshi players are seen in a huddle before taking the field. Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell are the openers for West Indies. Mustafizur Rahman has the new ball in hand and is ready to go...
... Second Innings ...

Bangladesh will be mightily disappointed with that batting display. They fell prey to the conditions early in the day and no one really showed any kind of stability at the top of the order. Tamim Iqbal did look like he would go on to build on the start he got but it wasn't meant to be. The only batter who really put up any fight was the skipper, Shakib Al Hasan who scored a quickfire fifty and managed to get his side over the 100-run mark. The visitors will have to bowl out of their skin to keep the opposition to a total as close to theirs as possible. An uphill climb for their bowlers awaits. Do join us for the second essay in a short while.

It has been an absolutely brilliant outing from the Windies pacers and they have managed to bundle out Bangladesh inside 33 overs! It was great intensity from the hosts right from the get-go and that has worked wonders for them. Kemar Roach gave them a brilliant start and the others built on it. They did give away a few runs but it was only a matter of time before Shakib Al Hasan mistimed one and he did just that and West Indies capitalized on it. Alzarri Joseph and Jayden Seales finished with three wickets each while Kyle Mayers too got a couple of important breakthroughs against the run of play. All in all, top performance from the hosts with the ball.

OUT! CAUGHT! Fuller this time, around off, Khaled Ahmed brings down a straight bat in defense but it takes a thick outside edge and flies straight into the hands of Nkrumah Bonner at fourth slip. Khaled Ahmed becomes the sixth batter for Bangladesh to bag a duck. The tourists are bundled out for just 103.
Commentary.Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: A touch short and outside off, Khaled Ahmed removes his bat from the line of the delivery.
Digs it in short, around off, Khaled makes a late leave.
Khaled Ahmed is the last man in for Bangladesh.

OUT! Shakib holes out! Alzarri Joseph angles in a length ball, around off, Shakib Al Hasan winds up for a big heave-ho over mid-wicket but ends up playing it a lot straighter. It flies down to widish long on and Kemar Roach takes the skier safely. End of a handy knock by the skipper. Bangladesh are nine down for just 103.
Commentary.Howout: c Kemar Roach b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Slightly short and on off, Shakib moves back and lofts it over cover-point. No run taken.
Negotiated safely. Ebadot Hossain gets right behind the line of the delivery and offers a dead bat in defense.
Jayden Seales gets a second warning from the umpire for running over the danger zone on his followthrough. He has to be really careful now.
Poor delivery. Down the leg side, an easy leave for the number 10. Jayden Seales receives a warning for running on the danger area.
Short and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a run. Again two balls to survive for Ebadot.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR SHAKIB! His 28th in Tests and 9th versus West Indies. It's been a good attacking knock from the skipper. Fuller and outside off, Shakib this time goes through the line and smashes it towards the long off fence. 100 up for Bangladesh!
Full in length, around middle, Shakib heaves it over mid-wicket and it falls wide of Kemar Roach running across to his left from wide long on. They decide not to run.
Too full in length and around off, Shakib squeezes it out through point and denies the single.

JUST SHORT! Back of a length, around middle, Ebadot Hossain is on his toes as he fends it away uncomfortably. The ball goes uppishly to short leg where Raymon Reifer is standing a shade deep. It falls in front of his outstretched hands.
Spears in a very full ball around off, Ebadot Hossain tries to defend but it whistles past the outside edge. After planting a leg gully, this delivery came as a surprise for the batter.
Short and on middle, Shakib rides the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg for a run. Two balls to survive for Ebadot Hossain and Shakib has a word with him.
Follows the batter down the leg side with a shortish delivery, Shakib turns it on the leg side. The ball rolls in the gap at mid-wicket but again Shakib doesn't run.
Short and on middle, Shakib steps back and cuts it to deep point and denies the single.
Alzarri Joseph digs it in short, around leg, Ebadot Hossain gets into a tangle as he awkwardly fends at it. It goes wide of the keeper and towards fine leg. They cross and Shakib returns on strike.

Smartly bowled. Jayden Seales senses the movement from the batter and slips a length ball down the leg side. Shakib shuffles across the stumps and then tries to flick. Misses. Ebadot Hossain will be on strike for the start of the next over.
Goes short and around leg, Ebadot Hossain fends it away and it goes down to fine leg. They take the single.
Angling in around off, on a length and shaping away, Ebadot Hossain tries to defend but misses.
Short and on middle, Shakib pulls it to deep square leg and looks for two. He realizes that the fielder has attacked the ball and sends Ebadot Hossain back eventually.

DROPPED! Nkrumah Bonner got a hand to it but failed to hang on. Jayden Seales delivers it on a length and outside off, Ebadot Hossain hangs his bat out and edges it to gully. Nkrumah Bonner dives across to his left, and attempts to catch it with one hand but it doesn't stick. The ball goes behind and they get a run. Good result for Bangladesh.
Darts a length ball on off, Ebadot blocks it well.

FOUR! Shakib decides to go for the boundary and shows no intention to take a single and retain strike. Back of a length, around off, Shakib rocks back and drags it wide of short mid-wicket. 12 from the over, Bangladesh are 7 away from touching 100.
FOUR! A touch short and on middle, angling in, Shakib heaves it over backward square leg and fetches a boundary. One ball left in the over for Shakib to retain strike.
Short and wide outside off, Shakib goes half-heartedly at it, as he attempts to cut. Gets a bottom edge and it doesn't carry to Joshua Da Silva.
Fuller and on middle, forced down towards long on. No run taken again.
Shortish and on off, Shakib steps back and dabs it to deep point. Doesn't take the run.
FOUR! Whacked away! Alzarri Joseph has been pretty ordinary with his length. Bowls it short and wide, Shakib has no qualms in putting it away to the deep point fence.
Slightly short and outside off, shaping away, Ebadot Hossain has a tame push at it and misses. Expect Shakib Al Hasan to farm strike from hereon.
Back of a length, around off, Hossain pushes inside the line and misses.
Ebadot Hossain is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mustafizur Rahman doesn't follow the plan and pays the price. Shakib was showing no confidence in him in the previous over, and it appeared the advice was to not flirt with anything not targeted at his body. Mustafizur Rahman follows this for three balls but loses his patience on the fourth ball. Finds a delivery drivable outside off and tries to showcase his talent. But his attempted drive results in an inside edge and Joshua Da Silva accepts yet another catch behind the stumps.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Angling away from the batter, on a length, Mustafizur Rahman is doing as told, not offering his bat.
Fuller and outside off, inviting the drive, Mustafizur Rahman stays back and lets it be.
Bouncer around leg, Mustafizur Rahman leans back and allows it through.
FOUR! Short again from Alzarri Joseph, this time it's wide outside off and Shakib latches onto it. He packs a punch and slaps it through backward point.
Shortish and around middle, Shakib shuffles back a bit but is cramped for room and is forced to defend it down.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it down safely.
That's unplayable. Alzarri Joseph bowls from round the wicket and serves a length ball around off. Shakib attempts to play the line but is beaten by the away movement.
Short and it's been pulled to deep square leg. Shakib denies the single.
Short ball on off, Shakib pulls it across the line but not in the gap.
Mustafizur Rahman comes in at number 9 for Bangladesh. Also, Alzarri Joseph will bowl from the opposite end.

OUT! Strangled down the leg side! Early success for West Indies in the session yet again and Bangladesh slip further. A pretty innocuous delivery, drifting down the leg side, on a length, Mehidy Hasan tries flicking but it takes a faint tickle from his bat and flies away to the keeper. Joshua Da Silva collects his third catch of the match and Bangladesh's total reads 77 for 7.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Goes full and in the line of the stumps, Shakib knocks it down to long on for one.
Make it four leaves in a row. Shakib has adopted a cautious approach to start.
Back of a length, around off and angling away, Shakib makes one more leave.
Lands it on a good length, wide outside off, another leave from Shakib.
Starts a new spell by angling away a length ball outside off, Shakib has nothing to do with it. He wants a sighter as of now.

We are back for the post-Lunch session on Day 1! The umpires and the players are on the field as Shakib Al Hasan and Mehidy Hasan make their way back to the middle. Jayden Seales to start proceedings with the ball after the interval.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

Right then, session one is done and West Indies seem to be in complete command at the moment. Bangladesh did get bowled out for 43 in the first innings the last time they played a Test match here but will want to put on some sort of a total on the board. Do join us for a riveting post-Lunch session coming up soon at 10.10 pm IST (4.40 pm GMT).

West Indies will be very happy with their exploits in the first session and the man who has the most wickets on this ground, Kemar Roach, was in full swing today as well. Roach picked up two wickets at the top and Jayden Seales too got one. Alzarri Joseph didn't quite find his length right but the introduction of Kyle Mayers after the Drinks break turned the momentum back in the hosts' favour and they are right on top of proceedings here. With the sun starting to shine and the ball getting a bit worn out, the Windies will want to pick up the remaining wickets at the earliest and not allow Shakib Al Hasan to have his way with the bat.

Bangladesh had the worst possible start as Mahmudul Hasan Joy fell for a golden duck in the very first over. After that the next couple of batters too went out without troubling the scorers, leaving the visitors reeling at 16/3! After this Tamim Iqbal and Litton Das did put up a fight and survived the first hour of the day. However, after the Drinks break both batters fell in quick succession and the wicket of Nurul Hasan meant Bangladesh were in deep trouble. Since then, the skipper Shakib Al Hasan has tried to counter-attack and has been effective to an extent as well. The hosts will try to muster up as many runs as possible now.

Session summary - 25 overs, 76 runs and 6 wickets! It has been an engrossing first session here on Day 1 and the hosts have certainly bossed it. They have picked up six wickets and have made full use of the pitch and conditions. West Indies now have a chance of bundling out the opposition in the next session itself.
Slightly short and turning away from Mehidy Hasan who lets it go. Gudakesh Motie concedes one run in the first over of his Test career and now, it's time for LUNCH on DAY 1.
Shakib Al Hasan skips forward, Gudakesh Motie bowls it full and on the pads, it's flicked behind square leg for a single.
On the pads once again and full, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to square leg.
Full on the stumps. Fended back to the bowler.
Pulls his length back slightly and bowls it outside leg. Shakib Al Hasan puts his pad to it and deflects it away.
Full on leg stump. Shakib Al Hasan dabs it to short leg.
Probably the last over before Lunch and it will be the debutant, Gudakesh Motie who will bowl it.
Fuller one and on off, Mehidy Hasan drives it straight towards the fielder at mid off.
On middle again, Mehidy Hasan defends it solidly.
Length ball down the leg side, Mehidy Hasan looks to flick it but the ball hits his thigh and rolls in front.
On middle this time and fuller in length, Mehidy Hasan eases it back towards Kemar Roach.
On a good length and on off, Mehidy Hasan defends it away.
On a length and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan waits for the ball and tries to cut. The ball goes towards the fielder at third man off the outside edge. Single taken.
Fuller one way wide outside off, Shakib Al Hasan doesn't bother it. Wide called.
Slower bouncer outside off, Shakib Al Hasan tries to pull it but mistimes it wide of mid-wicket and retains strike for the next over.
Slower ball flighted into the air. Yorker bowled wide on the off side and beats Shakib Al Hasan who tries to swing across the line and the wicket-keeper. Collected by first slip.
Short and really wide, Shakib Al Hasan steps back and cuts it to deep point for two runs.
Length ball on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Slower delivery once again, full and on off. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to backward point.
Back-of-the-hand slower delivery bowled on a yorker length outside off. Shakib Al Hasan swings hard at it but gets undone by the lack of pace as the ball hits the keeper's pads.
Goes fuller this time and angles it on the pads, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it towards square leg for one.
Shorter one again, Shakib Al Hasan looks to hit it but misses.

Slightly shorter and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play at it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and goes down towards the slip cordon. This was an excellent delivery from Kemar Roach.
A low full toss this time, outside off and dipping on the batter. Shakib Al Hasan drives it straight towards the fielder at short cover.
Shorter one on off, Shakib Al Hasan tries to play late and run it down to third man but finds third slip.
Touch fuller and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan gets on his knees and hits it over cover-point. The ball was in the air for a long time but falls in no man's land. A couple of runs are taken.
Fuller this time and asking Mehidy Hasan to drive from outside off stump. He does not oblige and leaves it alone.
Persists with the line outside off, Kyle Mayers bowls it again on a good length and Mehidy Hasan plays a similar shot to third slip.
Length ball bowled outside off, Mehidy Hasan knocks it along the ground towards backward point.
Full on off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to mid off for a single.
Full and bowled on off stump. Shakib Al Hasan is trying to give the bowler a charge and unsettle him but checks the shot and defends the ball close to his body towards covers.
Slightly full and outside off. Shakib Al Hasan takes a couple of steps forward and lets the ball go as it's angling away from him.
This is full and around off, Hasan punches it straight back past the bowler. The mid off fielder gives chase and keeps it down to a couple.
This is on the pads again and Hasan just nudges it towards square leg.
A touch fuller and angling on the pads, Hasan looks to glance it away but misses. The ball goes off the pads and rolls onto the leg side.
On middle this time, Mehidy Hasan guides it to the mid off region.
Fuller in length this time, Mehidy Hasan blocks it away.
Kemar Roach (5-2-13-2) is back on.

Chance for a run out, missed. Back of a length delivery, Shakib Al Hasan guides it towards point and calls for a single. The fielder collects it really well and has a shy at the end of the batter but misses. Mehidy Hasan gets a lucky escape.
Inswinger this time on a good length. Mehidy Hasan defends this and gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Full and down leg. Shakib Al Hasan misses the sweep and the keeper cannot collect it. Bangladesh get an extra run through a bye.

SIX! Connects this one really well! Shakib Al Hasan has been looking to go after Kyle Mayers all over and finally gets one off the middle of his bat. Full just outside off stump, Shakib Al Hasan makes room for himself and launches it over the long off boundary for a biggie!
Good-length delivery outside off stump, Shakib Al Hasan mistimes a cut shot towards cover.
On a good length outside off stump. Shakib Al Hasan tries to step across on the off side and paddle it fine. Misses the line of the delivery and is hit on his body.
In the channel outside off, Shakib walks forward for a big shot but it nips away to beat the outside edge.
Full and straight this time, this is worked away past square leg for a single.
Fuller, bowled with a bit of extra pace and down the leg side. Shakib looks to flick but misses.
On a length and wide outside off, Shakib Al Hasan lofts it over covers and gets a couple of runs.
On a length and down the middle, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly.
On middle, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it in front of square leg and immediately calls for two. Easily taken.

FOUR! That's mistimed in the air and Shakib Al Hasan has a narrow escape. Alzarri Joseph surprises the batter with a short ball that hurries on from the pitch. Shakib attempts to heave it across the line but it takes the top edge and flies behind mid on. Jayden Seales runs back and attempts to catch but it deflects off his hands and reaches the fence. A good attempt nonetheless. With Bangladesh in dire straits, this shot should be avoided by Shakib.
On a good length this time, angling into Mehidy Hasan who defends it with his gloves as the ball shoots up off the surface. Maiden over by Kyle Mayers.
Full and wide, Mehidy Hasan pushes at it and gets a thickish edge towards third slip. Doesn't carry.
Kyle Mayers continues bowling full and outside off stump. Mehidy Hasan is not sure which way it's going to move and plays at it tentatively. Beats the outside edge of his bat once again.
Full again and bowled wide outside off. Mehidy Hasan fends it awkwardly towards gully.
Full and outside off stump. This one swings outwards and beats Mehidy Hasan past the outside edge.
Full and outside off stump. Good shape into Mehidy Hasan who defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length this time and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone through and towards the keeper.
Sticks to his line bowling it outside off, Shakib Al Hasan guides it towards short cover.
Another one outside off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly.
Outside off this time and on a length, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play it towards covers but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and stays down.
Goes fuller again, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Fuller in length and down the leg side, Shakib Al Hasan looks to flick it but misses. It goes off his pads to the keeper.
Mehidy Hasan is the new man in.

OUT! LBW! Two wickets in the over for Kyle Mayers and the Windies are all over the opposition! Mayers goes a bit wider of the crease and angles in a big inswinger from well outside off. Nurul Hasan looks to pad it away but the ball does come a long way in. Huge appeal from the bowler and it is given. Hasan looks sheepishly at his skipper and does review it. No spike on UltraEdge as the ball is nowhere near the bat and Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the off stump. The onfield decision stays. Hasan goes for a duck and Bangladesh looking to bow out in a hurry here.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kyle Mayers

Commentary.Commentary: Nurul Hasan offers no shot and gets pinged on the pads, the umpire raises his finger. Hasan does review it. It is a fair delivery and UltraEdge confirms that there's no bat on it. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is outside off which doesn't matter as no shot is offered and the ball is going on to clip the top of off. The original decision stands, OUT!
FOUR LEG BYES! Attempts a yorker again but strays in line. Angling down leg and clips Nurul Hasan's pads on the way and goes down to the fine leg boundary.
Nurul Hasan is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Catastrophe! Litton Das follows Tamim Iqbal back to the pavilion and the Windies will have two new batters to bowl at. Kyle Mayers bowls this one on a length and angles it in from outside off. Das strides towards the ball and looks to play it off the front foot. It is the scrambled-seam delivery and the ball just holds its line, unlike the last delivery that swung away. Das gets a feather on it and this time Joshua Da Silva takes a simple catch behind the sticks. The visitors are now five down and Mayers gets a wicket in his very first over.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kyle Mayers

Commentary.Commentary: Full and shaping away beautifully. It's bowled slightly wide this time and beats the bat of Litton Das.
Yorker length, angling into the stumps. Litton Das digs it out to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off stump. Shaping away from Litton Das who hangs his bat and gets beaten.
The skipper, Shakib Al Hasan walks out to bat now. Also, Kyle Mayers comes into the attack.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Tamim Iqbal has got a faint edge on it and has to walk back. Alzarri Joseph speeds in and goes full and down the leg side. Iqbal looks to flick it away but once again it's the right leg that makes it look like he's falling over. The ball goes off the edge and to the right of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives across to his right and takes a sharp catch. Iqbal departs cheaply after a decent start and the visitors have to start all over again.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Change of length, goes shorter this time, Tamim Iqbal ducks underneath it.
Fuller and on middle, Iqbal defends it back towards Alzarri Joseph.
Touch full this time and on middle, Tamim Iqbal blocks it towards short cover.
Goes outside off this time and on a good length, Tamim Iqbal looks to defend it but misses.
Bowls a length ball on middle, Tamim Iqbal defends it back towards the bowler.

DRINKS! It's been a productive first hour for the hosts as Kemar Roach and Jayden Seales have sent three opposition batters back to the pavilion without even opening their accounts. The pair of Tamim Iqbal and Litton Das has done well so far to steady the ship a bit but neither of them has quite found the touch yet. West Indies will now be looking to repeat their showing with the ball and pick up a couple of more wickets before Lunch. It is very important for Bangladesh that the two batters currently at the crease stay there till the interval, at least.
Back of a length, on the fifth stump line. Litton Das lets it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Loose shot from Litton Das but he gets away with it. Length ball, landing on the grassy area outside off. Das goes chasing after it and gets a thick outside edge that flies over a jumping Jermaine Blackwood at third slip for a boundary.
Drifting onto the pads, Iqbal works it around the corner for a single.
Uppish but in the gap! Seales pitches it up around off and Iqbal looks to drive off the front foot. Iqbal punches it uppishly to the left of Alzarri Joseph at mid off and picks up a couple of runs
Length and angles in close to the off stump. Tamim Iqbal leaves it alone.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Seales floats it outside off and Tamim Iqbal leans into the cover drive and strokes it past the diving Alzarri Joseph to collect a boundary.
Short of a length, around off and it's another easy leave for Litton Das. Maiden.
Joseph keeps it on a slightly shorter length and the ball nips back in a touch from around off. Das shoulders his arms at it.
Hard length from Joseph, on off. Das camps back and dabs it down towards the point region.
On a good length, around the fifth stump line. Das doesn't offer a shot at it.
Pitches it up this time, a fair bit outside off. Das goes chasing after it as he looks to cover drive but misses the ball.
Too close for comfort. A length ball, angled in on off stump and just holding its line. Litton Das makes an assured leave.
This is on a fullish length but angling down the leg side. Tamim Iqbal lets it through to the keeper.
Shorter in length, around off. The ball shoots up a bit more than expected but Iqbal does well to keep it down.
Seales switches to around the wicket now and angles it on the pads, Iqbal works it off his legs towards the fine leg region. The batters get a couple of runs.
Goes full this time, but down the leg side. Tamim Iqbal looks to flick it away but misses.
Touch short again from Seales, around the body. Das hops and eases it onto the leg side for an easy single.
Seales digs in a short ball around leg, Tamim Iqbal gets hurried on but manages to fend it away past square leg for a single.
Jayden Seales (4-1-9-1) to operate from the other end now.
Around off, shaping away from a length, Litton Das has nothing to do with it again.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Better this time, on a length and outside off, shaping away, Das leaves. The length is right but he needs to bowl a lot closer to the stumps.
Again the length is slightly short and outside off, Das forces it off his back foot to point. Needs to pitch it further up with the surface offering some movement.
A touch short again, around off, Das rocks back to pull but mistimes his shot to mid on.
FOUR! Not the desired start from Alzarri Joseph. A gentle loosener. Back of a length, around off, Litton Das camps back and punches it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
First bowling change of the day as Alzarri Joseph comes in to replace Jayden Seales.
Quite wide outside off, shaping further away, Tamim Iqbal has nothing to do with it. Maiden.

That's loose from Tamim Iqbal. Fuller in length and wide outside off, Iqbal spots the chance for a big booming drive but only manages an inside edge. Luckily for him, he has not dragged it onto the stumps.
Close to off, on a length, Tamim is on the front foot as he pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Great lines from Roach. Pitching it on and around off, on a length and getting it to nip away. Tamim Iqbal strides forward and then allows it through.
The sky is getting gloomier by the minute now. This will continue to help the Windies pacers plus there's a strong wind blowing across the ground as well.
Not much movement on this delivery, on a length and outside off, Iqbal shoulders arms.
Outswinger outside off, on a length, Tamim covers his stumps and makes a leave.
Playing with the patience of the batter. Jayden Seales serves another one in the zone outside off, getting it to move away off the seam, Litton Das lifts his bat skywards and lets it go.
A little too straight in line on this occasion, Das leans across and flicks it in the gap at mid-wicket for two runs.

Jayden Seales pulls his length back as he bends his back. Around off and there is some steep bounce. Litton Das is on the back foot, trying to deal with it and keeps it out safely from the bottom half of his bat.
Hurls another length delivery in the region outside off, shaping away, Das allows it through.
This is good bowling. Jayden Seales repeats the last delivery, this time from the off stump line, Litton is forced to offer shot and he blocks it to the off side.
Pitches it up and outside off, nipping away, Litton Das makes a patient leave.
Just outside off, on a length and leaving the batter with the seam movement, Tamim shoulders arms.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, Litton works it down towards fine leg for a run.
Close to off this time, full and shaping in, Litton defends it near his front pad.
Roach pitches it up and lands an inswinger outside off. It's a tempter but Litton allows it through to the keeper.
Roach delivers it full and around middle, Tamim flicks it through mid-wicket and collects three runs. Tamim Iqbal completes 5000 runs in Test cricket!
Full in length, around off, Tamim gets on the front foot and defends it to the off side.
Short and wide outside off, it's left alone by Litton Das. A wicket maiden for West Indies!
In the channel outside off, on a length and shaping away, Das shoulders arms.
Angles in a length ball, around middle and leg. Das helps it off his pads to short mid-wicket.
Another outswinger from Jayden. This time though the line is too wide outside off and it's an easy leave for Litton Das.
Outswinger to greet the new batter. It's on a good length and close to off, Das pushes at it and misses.
Litton Das walks out to bat with Bangladesh in a spot of bother.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The poor batting form of Mominul Haque continues. He stepped down from captaincy to focus on his batting but it has not started well for him. Jayden Seales joins the party and Bangladesh are in a big spot of bother. The angle of Jayden does the trick. He serves it around off and on a length. Mominul Haque could have left it but has a feel for it inside the line with zero footwork. It kisses the shoulder of his bat and Jermaine Blackwood takes a sharp catch to his right at second slip.
Commentary.Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Jayden Seales

Commentary.Commentary: Bowls it quite wide outside off, on a length, Tamim strides forward and then offers no shot.
Fires it in, very full and on off, Tamim drives it down to mid off.
FOUR! Easy pickings. A little too straight from Roach, on a length and drifting down the leg side, Tamim clips it behind square leg and picks up his second boundary in the over.
This one is angled in from around off, Tamim is on the front foot in defense.
On a good length outside off, shaping away, Tamim lets it be.

FOUR! Tamim will play his shots if it's in his zone. Kemar Roach overpitches outside off, Tamim Iqbal leans into the drive and crunches it in front of square on the off side. Good timing and placement, a boundary results.
Around off, a touch full, Tamim presses forward with an angled bat and pushes it wide of the gully fielder. A single to end the over.

Howwzzatt? Perhaps missing the leg stump as the finger stays down. Jayden Seales serves an inswinger. He pitches it around leg and it nips back in to beat the attempted flick shot of Tamim Iqbal. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but to no avail.
Lands it on a good length, around middle, Tamim closes the face of his bat and helps it towards square leg.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Iqbal attempts to flick but misses. That was not too far away from the edge.
FOUR! Aerial but in the gap. Fuller in length, around middle, Tamim Iqbal flicks it with sweet timing and sends it racing away through mid-wicket for a boundary - first of this Test match.
Right on the money. Lands it on a length around off, Tamim Iqbal strides forward and defends it towards short mid-wicket.
Close to off and on a good length, Mominul sticks on the back foot and blocks it to the off side.
Fraction short and outside off, Mominul Haque allows it through safely to the keeper.

Roach goes very full and fires it around middle and leg. Mominul attempts to flick but misses. It clips his pads and rolls to the right side of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives to stop the ball. It's not cleanly done and the batters think about a run. Eventually, no one crossed.
Dishes out a length delivery in the channel outside off, Mominul covers the line and shoulders arms.
Back of a length, around middle and off, Mominul gets squared up a bit as he defends it down from the back foot.
Mominul Haque is in at number 4.

OUT! BOWLED! Off stump goes for a morning walk! Another Bangla batter bags a duck. Kemar Roach posing trouble with the 'round the wicket angle. He lands it around off, on a length and it skids on with the angle. Najmul Hossain Shanto comes forward to defend but is a bit late in bringing his bat down. The ball finds the gap and goes on to demolish the stumps. The leading wicket-taker in Test cricket at this venue is off to a great start. Roach is on fire!
Commentary.Howout: b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: A measured stroke from Iqbal. Too full and around off, Tamim Iqbal drives it straight back and Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks at the other end to allow the ball to go over him. The mid on fielder chases it down and they get a couple of runs.
And again. This one holds up a bit after landing on a length around middle. Tamim is early into the shot as he works it a shade uppishly towards mid-wicket.
Drifting down the leg side, on a good length, Tamim offers no shot. It brushes his pads and rolls away to the keeper.
Fuller and around off, a confident drive off the front foot by Tamim but he finds the fielder at short cover.

'CATCH IT' is the shout... but it falls short. Some moisture on the wicket and the ball is gripping. This one is around off, on a length, Tamim lunges and is early into his defensive shot. He ends up chipping it in the air but it falls in front of the mid on fielder.
The natural angle of the pacer beats the bat. Around off, angling away, Tamim Iqbal attempts to block but it whizzes past the outside edge.
Jayden Seales to share the new ball with Kemar Roach.
Bowls it in the right channel outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto is watchful as he lets it be. A successful start for Kemar Roach.
In the channel outside off, Shanto hangs back inside the crease and defends it with soft hands to the off side.
This time Shanto is on his toes and defends this delivery with the angle to the leg side.
Back of a length, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto stays on the back foot and lets it through to the keeper.
Najmul Hossain Shanto walks out to bat at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT! It's a golden duck for Mahmudul Hasan Joy. Roach switches to over the wicket for the right-hander and hurls across a length ball outside off. It lands and shapes back in a shade, again with some extra bounce. Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on the front foot, he has committed himself to the defensive shot. The ball hurries onto this blade, takes the outside edge and Nkrumah Bonner takes a nice diving catch to his right at gully.
Commentary.Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Tamim is away on the first ball, although in an unconvincing manner. Kemar Roach speeds in from 'round the wicket and gets a length ball to move back into the southpaw with extra bounce. Tamim tries to defend but it takes the inner half and runs behind square leg. They cross for a run.

Done with the pre-game formalities and it's time now to play. The Windies team is seen in a huddle as Kemar Roach presents Gudakesh Motie with his maiden Test cap and Motie becomes the 328th cricketer to represent the Windies in Test matches. The Bangladeshi openers, Tamim Iqbal and Mahmudul Hasan Joy take their guard as Kemar Roach has been handed the new ball and is raring to go. The Windies players and the Bangladeshi openers take the knee to show their support for the BLM movement. Let's play...

We are moments away from the start of play. But first, the two sets of teams line up for their respective national anthems. It will be Bangladesh's national anthem first followed by the national anthem of the West Indies. Also, Daryl Matthew, the minister of education of Antigua, says a few words and commemorates the start of the Test match.

PITCH REPORT - Sir Curtly Ambrose and Samuel Badree are pitchside. Badree says that a gayle-force wind is blowing across the ground and the pitch looks a bit strange. Sir Ambrose says that there is some grass around the edges of the pitch and it will be interesting to see how it plays. Badree says that it seems to be result oriented.

Shakib Al Hasan, the captain of Bangladesh, says they would have bowled first too but they don’t mind batting even though it will be tough in the first hour. He feels it will be good for them to bowl in the fourth innings as they have two spinners. He has confidence in his side as they have exciting fast bowlers and gives a special mention to Litton Das who he thinks has been playing well. Says it is time for them to put their hands up and play to their best abilities and gives respect to the West Indies team as he feels they have good players.

West Indies skipper, Kraigg Brathwaite says that they will bowl first, as the pitch has more moisture. Adds that Gudakesh Motie makes his debut and he's looking forward to the opportunity. Further says that they need to be more focused on this series and they have set higher standards for this series compared to the last one.

Bangladesh (Playing XI) - Tamim Iqbal, Mahmudul Hasan Joy, Shakib Al Hasan (C), Najmul Hossain Shanto, Mominul Haque, Litton Das, Nurul Hasan (WK), Mehidy Hasan, Mustafizur Rahman, Khaled Ahmed and Ebadot Hossain.

West Indies (Playing XI) - Kraigg Brathwaite (C), John Campbell, Raymon Reifer, Nkrumah Bonner, Jermaine Blackwood, Kyle Mayers, Joshua Da Silva (WK), Alzarri Joseph, Kemar Roach, Gudakesh Motie (On debut) and Jayden Seales.
TOSS - West Indies have won the toss and they will BOWL first.
Did you know? The last time Bangladesh played a Test in Antigua, they got bowled out for 43 in the first innings. West Indies ended up winning that game by an innings and 219 runs.

We are back for Bangladesh's second innings! The umpires and the West Indies players take their positions on the field. Tamim Iqbal and Mahmudul Hasan Joy are the openers for Bangladesh. Kemar Roach, as usual, has the new ball in hand and is raring to go.
... Third innings ...

It was a hard toil for Bangladesh. They sweat hard on the field but struggled to create breakthroughs. All the investments they did in the two sessions eventually paid rich dividends, especially when they took the second new ball. Mehidy Hasan was the focal point of their bowling as his 4-fer infused life in Bangladesh's bowling. Khaled Ahmed and Ebadot Hossain were also impressive and got rewarded with two wickets apiece. West Indies have gained a handy lead and the touring team will have to bat better than the last time to stay relevant in this Test match. Those grassy patches on the surface got nicely targeted by the Windies bowlers in the first innings, and expect them to do that again. Let's see how the Asian team responds...

Valuable runs from the bat of debutant Gudakesh Motie, and his knock played a critical role in taking West Indies' lead to 162 runs. It was a determined batting show by the hosts and the only thing they could have done better was to bat with more intent this morning. After consuming close to 113 overs, to score 265, in this era of Test cricket, looks a bit odd, especially on a good batting strip. Anyway, this is how they operate under Kraigg Brathwaite. Once again their skipper led from the front and formed important stands with Nkrumah Bonner and Jermaine Blackwood.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan rounds up a sensational outing with his fourth wicket to go along with a stunning catch. Hasan angles this one on a length, around off. Jayden Seales gets down on one knee, looking to sweep it away, but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Huge appeal and the finger is raised almost instantaneously. No harm in reviewing and Seales does just that. UltraEdge shows no bat is involved and Ball Tracking comes up with three reds. West Indies have been bundled out for 265 runs and have a first-innings lead of 162 runs!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Jayden Seales has been adjudged out LBW but given that it is the last wicket, he reviews it. UltraEdge is checked first and there's no spike on it. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is in line and the ball is going on to hit the middle stump. The original decision of OUT stands and the West Indies innings comes to an end.
On off this time, Jayden Seales defends it towards the fielder at silly point.
Goes fuller on middle and leg, Jayden Seales blocks it towards the fielder at short leg.
Outside off this time, Jayden Seales defends it towards the fielder at point.
Bowls fuller and on off, Gudakesh Motie eases it to short covers and takes a quick single.
Good-length delivery this time on middle and off, Gudakesh Motie taps it towards point and runs across to retain strike.

FOUR! Up and over! Khaled Ahmed gets this full on off and Gudakesh Motie makes room and heaves it over mid off. The ball bounces before the boundary and rolls towards it. The fielder is unable to pull it ball and and concedes a boundary!
Full toss on off, Jayden Seales defends with soft hands towards cover and rushes across for a single.
Yorker length outside off stump, Jayden Seales gets bat to it and bumps the ball towards second slip.
Full and outside off, the natural angle taking it away from Jayden Seales who leaves it alone.
Jayden Seales is the last man in for West Indies.

OUT! TAKEN! A stunner from Mehidy Hasan and Khaled Ahmed strikes with the first ball of his new spell. Ahmed steams in and delivers it halfway down the track, outside off. It is there to be hit and Jermaine Blackwood goes after it. Blackwood tries to force it off the back foot over covers but doesn't quite get his timing right. The ball is hit hard and to the left of short cover where Mehidy Hasan dives to his left and pouches it out of thin air. Blackwood is left stunned but has to walk back after a fine knock. The lead currently stands at 155 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Mehidy Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Khaled Ahmed is brought back into the attack as he replaces Ebadot Hossain.
Lands it on off this time, Gudakesh Motie guides it to covers. They had a chance for a single but they decide not to take it.
Bowls it fuller and down the leg side, Gudakesh Motie flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
Outside off again from Mehidy Hasan, left alone by Gudakesh Motie.
Outside off with a hint of turn, Gudakesh Motie eases it towards point.

NOT OUT! Close but not close enough and for now, Gudakesh Motie will keep on batting. Mehidy Hasan slides this one on a length and angles it into middle. Gudakesh Motie looks to defend it off the front foot but seems to have misses it and the ball goes on to crash into the pads. Bangladesh seem certain that it is out and go up in unison but the appeal is turned down. Shakib reviews it but UltraEdge shows that the ball took the inside edge before hitting the pads. Review lost then for Bangladesh.

A huge shout for LBW but the umpire remains unmoved. Shakib Al Hasan does go for the review at the last second. The third umpire first checks the UltraEdge and finds that the ball clearly took the inside edge. The on-field decision of NOT OUT stands.
Goes fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the leg side and takes a single.
Length delivery on leg stump, Gudakesh Motie works it towards leg gully and Jermaine Blackwood refuses a single.
Full and wide down leg side. Gudakesh Motie leaves it alone.

FOUR! Wow! This is some exciting batting from Gudakesh Motie and he is getting applause from the vice-captain as well. Pitched up, around off. Motie stands tall and just drives on the up, creaming it through extra cover for yet another boundary. The lead is now over 150 runs and that could be a huge psychological advantage for West Indies.
Good-length delivery on middle. Gudakesh Motie blocks this back to the bowler.
Ebadot Hossain gets this closer and on a good length. Gudakesh Motie judges it well and lets it go.

FOUR! Thickish outside edge! Ebadot Hossain delivers this wide from off and full, Gudakesh Motie decides to go for the expansive drive over covers but instead gets a thick outside edge that flies past the slip cordon for a boundary. Jermaine Blackwood pats Gudakesh Motie on the back and seems happy with the shot.
Goes fuller and on off, Gudakesh Motie looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards the third man. They collect three runs off it, brilliant running.
Shakib Al Hasan calls for an extra helmet onto the field and now there's silly point as well as short leg in place for the debutant.

FOUR! Gudakesh Motie is off the mark in Test cricket and what a way to do it! Bowls it outside off, Gudakesh Motie opens the face of the bat and cuts it past the backward point for a boundary. The lead grows to 141 now.
On middle again, Gudakesh Motie eases it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Gudakesh Motie defends it solidly.
On middle and fuller, Jermaine Blackwood hits it straight and hard but finds the fielder at long on. He takes a single.
Fuller in length and down the middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the leg side.
Bowls it down leg side once again from a good length. Nurul Hasan does well to collect the moving ball by diving to his right.
Ebadot Hossain continues bowling good length but gets his radar off. This one is bowled wide from leg stump and Gudakesh Motie lets it go.
Gudakesh Motie gets a back-of-a-length delivery on middle to welcome him to Test cricket. He goes back and defends it well.
Gudakesh Motie, the debutant, is the next man in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The hard work is finally paying off for the Bangladesh bowlers and West Indies are going down in a hurry here. Ebadot Hossain goes full and outside off, inviting the drive from Kemar Roach who just doesn't have the ability of a top-order batter to not give in to the temptation. Roach gets a thick outside edge that flies to the right of third slip where Litton Das takes a very good catch. Just the two wickets remain now for West Indies and Bangladesh will be looking to clean up the tail soon.
Commentary.Howout: c Litton Das b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: Ebadot Hossain attacks the leg stump from a good length. Jermaine Blackwood works it to deep square leg for a single.
Good-length ball outside off. Ebadot Hossain is getting good shape away and Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Fuller in length and on off with a hint of turn, Kemar Roach leans forward and defends it away.
Kemar Roach is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another sharp catch from Nurul Hasan behind the stumps and Mehidy Hasan is in the groove now. This is fuller and a bit quicker, around off. Alzarri Joseph goes on the back foot instead of playing it off the front foot. Joseph looks to play for the turn that isn't there as the ball goes straight on. He gets a thick outside edge straight into the keeper's mitts and his stay at the crease is a short one. West Indies lead by 135 runs with just 3 wickets in hand now.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Similar to the last delivery, this is again flicked towards the fielder at the short mid-wicket region.
On middle and fuller in length, Alzarri Joseph flicks it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
On off this time, Alzarri Joseph guides it to the short cover fielder.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood pushes it towards long on and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, Alzarri Joseph does not offer any shot.

Almost chops that one back onto the stumps. Ebadot Hossain bowls it on a good length and angles it in from off stump. Jermaine Blackwood gets an inside edge past the stumps and gets a single to fine leg.
Pulls the length back, and bowls it wide, Jermaine Blackwood goes for the expansive cut and is fortunate to not get bat on it. Bangladesh players appeal in unison but there is nothing to it.
Even wider this time and full, Jermaine Blackwood watches it pass him and go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on off, Jermaine Blackwood gets back and defends it towards mid off.
Ebadot Hossain (25-8-55-1) to resume his spell from the opposite end.
On a shorter length with a hint of turn into the right-hander, Alzarri Joseph blocks it well.

Fuller in length and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood nudges it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single. A better throw at the keeper's end and Alzarri Joseph would have been struggling to make it in time but it is a well-judged run in the end.
Fuller in length and on middle, this is flicked towards the mid-wicket region.
FOUR! Poor delivery this, dragged down on middle. Jermaine Blackwood pulls it hard and thumps it past square leg for a boundary.
On middle again, Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the mid on fielder.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it to the fielder at short mid-wicket.

We are back for the final session on Day 2! A lot happened in the post-Lunch session and the game is now moving along swiftly with Bangladesh having a real shot at keeping the Windies lead to well under 200 runs. The umpires and the players make their back to the middle with Alzarri Joseph and Jermaine Blackwood set to resume their innings. Shakib Al Hasan is seen leading his side in a huddle before taking the field. It is going to be Mehidy Hasan to continue his effective spell after the break.
... Day 2, Session 3 ...

Session summary - 25 overs, 72 runs and 3 wickets! Bangladesh have finally been able to make inroads in the second session on Day 2 as they picked up three wickets. Khaled Ahmed bowled aggressively and got rid of the opposition skipper before he could get to his century which was a huge moment in the innings. It was then the spell from Mehidy Hasan towards the end of the session that saw him pick up a couple of quick wickets and he has given Bangladesh a chance of running through the West Indies tailenders. West Indies on the other hand have started scoring at a better rate but Jermaine Blackwood has found himself lucky a couple of times. Blackwood has the runs in his kitty but is running out of partners. It is now up to him to anchor the innings and take the hosts to a big lead which currently stands at 128 runs. Join us for an exciting final session on Day 2 at 12.30 am IST (7 pm GMT, the previous day).
Ebadot Hossain brings the length back, and continues to bowl on off, Alzarri Joseph stands up tall and defends it well. The umpire takes the bails off and it will be Tea on DAY 2.
Inswinger outside off, bowled on a good length. Alzarri Joseph decides to leave it last minute.
Good-length delivery on middle-off, Alzarri Joseph looking solid in his defensive approach.
Goes outside off and full. Alzarri Joseph is happy to leave it alone.
Ebadot Hossain goes full on off stump. Alzarri Joseph defends this firmly back to the bowler.
Back-of-a-length delivery, angled into the body. Jermaine Blackwood works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Similar to the last delivery on leg, Alzarri Joseph flicks it towards the fielder at leg gully.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Alzarri Joseph defends it towards the fielder at short leg.
Fuller in length drifting away from the batter, Alzarri Joseph looks to defend it but misses.
Goes fuller and outside off, Alzarri Joseph guides it to point and straight to the fielder.
Alzarri Joseph is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A sharp catch behind the sticks by Nurul Hasan and Mehidy Hasan is turning it on here for his side. Lovely flight and on a nagging length as well, close to the off stump. Joshua Da Silva looks to defend off the front foot but is beaten in flight and the ball just holds its line as well. The outside edge is found and Nurul Hasan makes no mistake. The finger-wag celebration is out from Mehidy Hasan and Da Silva walks back without troubling the scorers much.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Tossed up down the leg side, Joshua Da Silva flicks it towards the fielder at leg slip.

FOUR! Hammered away and that will be FIFTY for Jermaine Blackwood, his slowest in this format of the game. Length ball, around off, Blackwood hangs back and just crunches this one through wide mid off for a boundary. Ebadot Hossain smiles back at the batter in disbelief as Blackwood raises his bat.
Full this time wide from off stump. Joshua Da Silva works it to point and gets off the mark.
Good-length delivery on middle this time. Joshua Da Silva defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood manages to work this to third man for a single.

Ebadot Hossain is on fire. Brings the line closer this time on a good length and it is unplayable as the ball shapes away beautifully. Bangladesh players are convinced there is an edge but the umpire disagrees. They will not review and that is the right decision.
What a beauty from Ebadot Hossain! Bowls on a good length outside off. Gets movement away and extra bounce and beats Jermaine Blackwood all ends up.
Length delivery angling it into the batter, Joshua Da Silva opens the face of the bat and blocks it away. Wicket-maiden from Mehidy Hasan.
Bowls it fuller in length, Joshua Da Silva flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Fuller one and down the middle, Joshua Da Silva blocks it back towards the bowler.
On middle again, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Joshua Da Silva eases it towards the mid on region.
Joshua Da Silva is in next.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan just loves bowling to Kyle Mayers and this is the fourth time that he has dismissed him. This is on a length, around middle and leg and seems to be going on with the angle. Mayers looks to block it off the front foot but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal and the keeper seems certain but the umpire is unmoved. It is reviewed by Shakib and UltraEdge confirms that it is pad first and then the ball hit the bat. Ball Tracking shows that the ball straightened and would have gone on to crash into the leg stump. Brilliant review this time from Bangladesh and they have another wicket in this session.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Huge appeal from behind the stumps for an LBW decision but the umpire doesn't seem interested. Shakib Al Hasan does go for the review this time. The third umpire checks UltraEdge first and the ball seems to have hit both the bat as well as the pad but it is pad first. Ball Tracking comes up with three reds and the on-field decision is overturned to OUT! Kyle Mayers is a goner.
Loopy full toss on off. Jermaine Blackwood tries to make the most of it but mistimes it to covers.
Length ball wide from off stump. Jermaine Blackwood slashes at it and misses as it goes under his bat towards the keeper.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off. There is a bit of an extra bounce but Kyle Mayers does well to fend it away past point and pick up a single.
FOUR! Punched away with authority! Ebadot Hossain bowls short again and gives Kyle Mayers some room. He leans back on the backfoot and thumps it through covers for a boundary!
Good-length delivery on leg stump. Jermaine Blackwood glances it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Streaky boundary! Ebadot Hossain starts with a short and wide loosener. Jermaine Blackwood slashes at it hard and gets a thick outside edge over the slip cordon for an unconvincing boundary!
Ebadot Hossain (22-8-38-1) is back on.
On a length and just outside off, Kyle Mayers leaves it alone. The ball just aired past the off pole and towards the keeper.
Fuller in length and on middle, Kyle Mayers defends it back towards the bowler.
Much fuller in length, Jermaine Blackwood drives it towards long on and rotates the strike.
Touch fuller on middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood blocks it towards the vacant short leg region.
Goes fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Length again, spilled down the leg side as Mayers misses the flick.
On a length, around the top of off. This is pushed out towards mid on.
Back of a length, around middle. This is worked off the back foot behind square on the leg side for an easy single.

Almost! Khaled Ahmed keeps on being aggressive and bowls it short this time, at the body. Jermaine Blackwood looks to pull this one but gets hurried on and gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. The ball almost trickles back onto the stumps but Blackwood manages to get his right boot on the ball in time. Living dangerously here, Blackwood.
Full and wide of the off pole, left alone by Blackwood.
Back of a length, around off. Blackwood hops and keeps it out on the off side.
Shorter in length and turning onto the pads, Blackwood tucks it away fine through short fine leg for a single.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Blackwood leans forward to defend.
On a length, at the stumps. This is pushed down to mid on.

Huge appeal this time but the finger stays down. On a length, around off and turning in quite a fair bit. Jermaine Blackwood strides out to nudge it on the leg side but misses and gets rapped on the pads. After some thinking, Shakib Al Hasan decides not to review it. Oh, no! The replay shows that it would have been curtains for Blackwood had it been reviwed. Another poor decision from Bangladesh and this might cost them a lot.
Quicker and flatter, around off. This is defended off the back foot.
Flighted, on a good length and around off. The ball bounces a bit extra as it turns into the batter. Blackwood does well to adjust and fend it away.

Stifled appeal from the keeper but nothing doing says the umpire. This is full and around off, Kyle Mayers looks for the expansive cover drive but gets beaten past the outside edge. There is a noise but probably the bat hit the ground. The bowler seems confident but they don't opt for the review. The replay confirms that there was no spike as the ball went past the bat.
This is slanted across the left-hander and no shot is offered by Mayers.
Probing line once again from Khaled Ahmed. On a fuller length and pretty close to the off stump, Kyle Mayers makes an assured leave.
Nicely bowled. Fuller and into the channel around off, Kyle Mayers lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a good length, on the body. Blackwood works it off his hips behind square on the leg side for one.
This is pitched up on off, Blackwood solidly defends it off the front foot.
Mehidy Hasan spears this one into the batter's toes as Kyle Mayers digs it out back towards the bowler.
Fuller and a bit wider of the off pole, Blackwood strokes it towards cover-point and collects a single.
Tossed up this time, on middle. Blackwood nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Nicely bowled! Quicker, and angling in from around off. The ball skids on and Blackwood manages to work it towards mid-wicket.
On middle, flicked towards mid-wicket and Blackwood says no to the risky single.
A bit quicker and around off, Blackwood blocks it out.
On a good length, at the stumps and there's a bit of an extra bounce on this occasion. Mayers does well to fend it away.
This is banged in outside off, Mayers leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a good length, on leg. This is turned off the hips towards deep square leg for a run.
On a good length just outside off, keeps a touch low and Jermaine Blackwood gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Khaled Ahmed goes slightly back of a length angling into the body. Jermaine Blackwood works it awkwardly to point.

DRINKS! So, a wicket against the run of play for Bangladesh and they will now be pumped up as the Windies skipper is sent back to the pavilion. West Indies have a sizeable lead already but they must be careful not to lose their concentration and keep on batting if they are to maximize their opportunity. The visitors though will be hoping that one wicket brings two and so on. With that being said, Kyle Mayers walks out to bat.

Kraigg Brathwaite looks to work it onto the leg side and hops to do so but the ball keeps a shade low and Brathwaite gets pinged on the pads. A huge appeal from the bowler and the dreaded finger is raised. The skipper falls 6 runs short of what would have been another stellar hundred but it's time for some respite for Bangladesh. We are back for the post-Lunch session on Day 2! The players are out in the middle and Kraigg Brathwaite along with Jermaine Blackwood is set to his resume his stay at the crease. It's going to be Shakib Al Hasan who will start off with his left-arm orthodox spin after the interval.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Right then, we've had four sessions of Test cricket and West Indies have pretty much won all of them. The match certainly seems to be result-oriented and the hosts will now look to get through Day 2 with a sizeable lead in the bank. Bangladesh however need a big effort in the field to turn the tables. It doesn't seem easy to do as the pitch does seem to have eased out for the batters. The post-Lunch session starts at 10.10 pm IST (4.40 pm GMT). Do join us then for another cracking session.

The Bangladeshi pacers were unlucky last evening and did probe well but it has been the spin of Shakib Al Hasan that troubled the opposition batters this morning. After missing out on a couple of opportunities to get rid of Nkrumah Bonner, Shakib did get the breakthrough and Bangladesh would have liked to build on it. It hasn't happened though and even the edges that have been few and far in between, seem to be falling short. They will need to create more wicket-taking opportunities in the next session to avoid toiling under the hot sun for the entirety of the day and not only that, they need something to give in order to keep the Windies' lead to as low as possible.

Session summary - 31 overs, 64 runs and one wicket. Yet another session of Test cricket has flown by and West Indies certainly seem to have everything under control at the moment. Even though the scoring rate has been slow on Day 2 as well, the hosts have started to build up a decent lead which currently stands at 56 runs. Skipper Kraigg Brathwaite has surpassed the fifty-run mark and he will now be looking to inject a bit of momentum in their innings. Nkrumah Bonner looked a bit edgy this morning and was finally sent back to the hut by Shakib. Since then, Jermaine Blackwood has lent good support to the skipper and the pair has generally found it comfortable to negotiate the bowlers.

West Indies lead by 31 runs.

Drinks break. West Indies continue to be on top and are now in the lead by 30 runs. Their eight wickets remain intact. Bangladesh bowled well but without any rewards. Nkrumah Bonner offered them a couple of opportunities but Bangladesh didn't appeal when there was an edge and then neither Najmul Hossain Shanto nor Nurul Hasan went for the catch when there was a thick outside edge. The tourists have themselves to blame at the moment. The only solace for them is that the hosts have not yet run away with the game due to their slow scoring rate. Will the picture change in the next hour? Let's find out.

FOUR! Khaled hurls across a surprise short delivery, around middle, Nkrumah Bonner plays a reactive pull shot and times it well behind square leg. Ebadot Hossain moves across to his left in the deep but fails to cut it off. Should have done better.
Pitches it up and around off, Bonner punches it down to mid off.
Angling in, from a length around off, once again it's defended off the front foot to mid on.
Fuller and on off, defended from the middle of the bat to mid on.
A length ball is sliding down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to flick but misses. Stays on 49!
The line goes straighter this time, Brathwaite tucks a length ball through mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR! First boundary of this morning session and West Indies now move in the lead. Too full in length, around off, Kraigg Brathwaite squeezes it out past backward point for a boundary.
Full again, outside off, Kraigg is on the front foot this time as he defends it to the off side.
Fuller in length and outside off, Brathwaite decides to defend it from the back foot. Not a great choice given that Ebadot has the ability to bring the ball back in.
100 up! Back of a length, around middle and leg, Bonner nudges it down to fine leg for a run.
Too full and on off, defended back solidly.
Shortish and wide outside off, Brathwaite flashes and misses.
Sliding down the leg side, it's worked with the angle to the leg side.
On a length around middle, Bonner brings down a straight blade and defends it off the inner half. It rolls towards mid-wicket and they rotate the strike.
Fuller again, around off, Kraigg uses the angle of the bowler and eases it to the left side of mid on. A single is pinched.
Khaled begins his fresh spell by spearing a full ball on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite leans across and flicks it on the leg side, finds mid-wicket.
Khaled Ahmed (9-4-15-0) replaces Mustafizur Rahman from this end.

Unplayable! What a delivery! Ebadot dishes out a length delivery close to off, Nkrumah Bonner decides to play the trajectory of the ball but it straightens just a hint to beat the outside edge. Excellent over from Ebadot. The replays, later on, show that there was a spike. No one appealed. Strange.
Pitches it on a good length and outside off, Nkrumah Bonner presses forward to cover the line and then shoulders arms.
Loose from Nkrumah Bonner, a bit uncharacteristic from him. Short in length and outside off, holding its line, Bonner tries to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce.
Brought the last delivery in and this time around, Ebadot hurls across a length ball that holds its line outside off. Bonner leaves.
Beautiful delivery. This one lands on a length around off and nips back in sharply. Bonner fails to defend and is hit on the thigh pad. It then deflects behind towards the keeper.
Slightly short in length, close to off, Nkrumah Bonner stands tall on the back foot and defends it down on the pitch.
The Fizz comes from over the wicket for the final delivery. Lands it on a length around leg, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it calmly to the leg side.
Solid in defense. Around off, on a length, Kraigg gets half-forward and defends it to the off side.
Angling down the leg side, on a length, Brathwaite works it off his pads but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Slants in a length ball on off, this time Kraigg is more confident in his stance as he covers the line and blocks it back.
Fuller this time, around off and shaping in, Kraigg Brathwaite is forward in defense and it goes off the inner edge to mid-wicket.
Wrong line. This one lands on a length around middle and angles down the leg side. Bonner clips it behind square leg and picks up a single.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite keeps his weight on the back foot and defends it with an angled bat to cover-point.
In the channel outside off, Bonner plays it from the crease and finds the gap at point for one.

A bit of indecision this time. Ebadot Hossain delivers it on a length and outside off, Bonner takes a late call of leaving it. He though fails to withdraw his bat and it goes off the bottom half to the off side.
This time Ebadot angles in a full ball around off, forcing the batter to play, Bonner brings a straight bat down and pushes it defensively back to the bowler.
Zippy delivery. Skidding off the surface from a length outside off, Nkrumah Bonner offers no shot.
Pitches it up and outside off, Bonner drives it crisply to the left of the cover fielder. He dives and stops the ball, thereby stopping the batters in their tracks.

And again! Length ball, around off, the ball shoots up a bit more than usual but Brathwaite does well to keep it down on the off side. Consecutive maidens to start off the day by the Bangladeshi pacers.
Mustafizur Rahman looks to attack the pads this time but spills it down the leg side, Brathwaite leaves it alone and the keeper collects it safely.

A hint of extra bounce on this occasion. Fullish delivery, angling in from around off. Brathwaite looks to defend it under his eye line but gets a bit surprised by the bounce. He cops a blow on his gloves.
Back of a length, around off. Brathwaite looks to punch it off the back foot but his feet don't move much and Brathwaite mistimes it back onto the deck.
Slower in pace and angled into middle, Brathwaite stays in his crease and defends it back to the bowler.
Mustafizur Rahman starts from around the stumps and angles in a length ball on off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out off the front foot.
Mustafizur Rahman to share the attack from the opposite end.
Maiden to start with! A touch fuller and outside off, easy leave for Nkrumah Bonner.
On a length again, but a bit outside the line of off stump, Bonner shoulders arms at it.
BEATEN! Probing delivery from Ebadot Hossain, length, outside off and shaping back in quite a fair bit. Nkrumah Bonner has to play at it and gets beaten past the outside edge.
On a driving length but on the fifth stump line, Bonner watches it all the way through and decides not to play at it.
The length is pulled back this time and it is bowled pretty wide outside off, Bonner lets it through to the keeper.
Nice shape! Ebadot Hossain starts off with a fuller-length delivery from wide of the crease. The ball shapes back in nicely from outside off as Nkrumah Bonner defends it out solidly.

Time to get underway! The sun is presently out and there is a steady breeze blowing across the stadium. The conditions look ripe for batting and if the batters see off the first 30 minutes safely, they can get big runs here. Kraigg Brathwaite and Nkrumah Bonner are the overnight batters. The latter will be on strike as Ebadot Hossain gets ready to serve the first over of the day. Here we go...

Pitch report - Darren Ganga mentions that the moisture from Day 1 isn't there anymore but the conditions are similar and the spinners might come into play a bit more. Sir Curtly Ambrose joins him and says that the West Indies got the better part of the day to bowl but the intent to score runs wasn't there from their batters and he hopes that changes on Day 2.

Alzarri Joseph comes up for a quick word. The tall pacer says that he enjoyed bowling with the red ball after coming back from the white-ball format. Adds that there is always room for improvement and he could have been a touch fuller with his length. Mentions that he doesn't try to follow in anyone's footsteps and looks to create his own way. States that the pitch got better in the evening and feels that Day 2 should be the best day for batting.

While we wait for proceedings to begin on Day 2, England are taking on Netherlands in a one-day game where the English batters, riding on tons from Philip Salt, Dawid Malan and Jos Buttler have put on a world record score of 498 runs on the board. With the white ball game getting more and more batting oriented, will this record score ever be broken?

The hosts on the other hand will be mightily pleased with their exploits of Day 1 with all four pacers putting on a strong showing and getting rewarded thoroughly. On the batting front, runs were hard to come by for West Indies though but skipper Kraigg Brathwaite has held up one end really well. With the hosts trailing by just 8 runs and the wicket easing out, it could go from bad to worse for the visitors and they will need wickets in the first session to have some sort of say in the game. Will the Windies pile on the pressure and score big? Or will Bangladesh make some sort of a comeback? Find out as the first session is coming up in some time.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 2 of the first Test between West Indies and Bangladesh. The visitors were bundled out for 103 with six batters getting out without troubling the scorers which meant for the first time in the history of Test cricket that a side had six batters out for a duck in back-to-back matches. The skipper, Shakib Al Hasan was the only bright spark in their innings and even their bowlers had to toil hard to get a couple of breakthroughs.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Right then, West Indies hold all the aces heading into the second day. Their bowlers earned them the advantage and now it's the turn of their batters to extend it further and corner Bangladesh even more. Can they bat the touring team out of this Test match? Find out on Day 2 with action starting at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT). Our build-up however will begin much sooner. Do join us then, take care and goodbye!

Kemar Roach (8-2-21-2) comes up for a quick chat. The speedster says that they adjusted well as the pitch was tough to adjust, in terms of length. Talks about the grassy patch and mentions that they tried to hit those areas. Feels that winning the toss was important and shares that it's always best to bowl first in Antigua. Adds that it's a tough pitch to bat on and praises Kraigg Brathwaite for leading them well. Hopes to fight hard on Day 2 and get a good lead.

It was a hard toil for the Bangladeshi bowlers but they bowled really well. It's just that they didn't have luck on their side and a couple of missed opportunities in the field too have cost them. With batting conditions almost certainly to get better, it could be a long and hard day for them if they don't manage to pick up early wickets. Mustafizur Rahman was simply sensational and Ebadot Hossain probed well but they could only pick up a couple of wickets in total to go with their poor batting performance from earlier in the day.

West Indies lost a couple of wickets in the final session and only managed to score 80 runs in 33 overs. Given the pitch conditions, they would rather have wickets in hand for Day 2 as the pitch will get better for batting then. Kraigg Brathwaite as usual has been the rock for his team and has faced 149 balls for his 42. It will be interesting to see if he can build on the start and score a bit more freely. John Campbell and Raymon Reifer looked good for a bit at the top of the order but got out. Nkrumah Bonner is out there and will be looking to put on a big stand with his skipper come Day 2.

Day 1 of the first Test between West Indies and Bangladesh has flown by and the hosts trail by just 8 runs with 8 wickets in hand. It has been a day that has belonged to the bowlers as a total of 12 wickets fell throughout the course of the day. 10 of those wickets though belonged to the Windies quicks and that has now put them in pole position.
Mustafizur Rahman lets out a huge grunt and hurls across a full ball around off, Kraigg Brathwaite presses forward and defends it back solidly. That's Stumps on Day 1.
Switches back to 'round the wicket and darts in a full ball on off, Kraigg is on the front foot as he blocks it from the inner half of his bat. Last ball of the day coming up now...
Down the leg side, on a length, Kraigg Brathwaite has pulled down the shutter and shoulders arms.
The Fizz returns to over the wicket. He goes wide of the crease to deliver a length ball around off. It's angling away and Kraigg does well to defend it back.
Bumper this time, to keep the batter honest. Around leg and Kraigg Brathwaite allows it through to the keeper.
Sliding down the leg side, on a good length, Bonner eases it towards square leg for a run.
Flatter and shorter on off, punched wide of the cover fielder for one. The deficit for West Indies is 9 runs. Can they wipe it off before Stumps?
Shakib pulls his length back and delivers it outside off, Bonner is on the back foot as he slaps it to sweeper cover for a couple.
Fullish and on off, stroked off the front foot to mid off.
Tossed up and wide outside off, it's left alone.
Nicely flighted, it's full and around off, Bonner drives it past the bowler to mid off.
Perhaps an arm ball, around middle and leg, Kraigg nudges it behind square leg for a run.
With just 5 minutes or so left for the play to end, Shakib Al Hasan brings himself back on.
Bouncer around leg, Nkrumah Bonner sits underneath it with ease.
Dishes a length ball around off, straightening off the seam a touch, Nkrumah Bonner stays back to push inside the line. He edges it past the gully fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Goes very full and lands it around off, Bonner brings his bat down and defends it to mid on.
Stifled appeal for an lbw, too high and going down as well. This one starts from the middle stump line, on a length, Bonner is beaten while trying to flick and is rapped on the font pad.
That's a snorter. Mustafizur Rahman bends his back and digs it in around off. Nkrumah Bonner jumps on the back foot as he pushes inside the line and misses.
Shout for an lbw again, this time a bit muted one. Mustafizur Rahman serves it on a length, around middle and leg, Bonner tries to defend but misses. He is pinged on the pads. Going down, surely.
Around middle and spinning down, Kraigg moves back and works it off his pads. Finds short fine leg.
Flighted and full, around off, defended safely once more.
Full and floated, around off, it's blocked calmly off the front foot.
Loopy and full, outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite gets forward and across before defending it down.
Slightly short again, Kraigg goes back and helps it to mid-wicket.
A bit short and on off, Kraigg moves back and flicks but finds short leg.
Fuller and outside off, it's driven off the front foot but straight to mid off. Another maiden from Mustafizur Rahman.
Good areas from the Fizz. Keeps probing around off, fuller in length, Bonner gets behind the line and defends it off the front foot.
A touch short, on middle and drifting down, Nkrumah Bonner turns it on the leg side but finds square leg.
Lands it on a length and just outside off, holding its line, Bonner shoulders arms.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.

Huge shout for an lbw, the finger stays down. Shakib is off the field, Litton Das is in charge and he gets convinced to take the DRS. Mustafizur Rahman speeds in from 'round the wicket and angles in a full ball around middle. It skids on with the angle as Nkrumah Bonner tries to defend it with a straight bat but misses. The appeal is not entertained and the Ball Tracking shows that it's missing the stumps. Bangladesh lose one more review.
Mustafizur Rahman (9-5-7-1) comes in to replace Ebadot Hossain.
The line is straighter, the length is fuller, it's clipped with the spin through mid-wicket for a run.
Around off, on a fuller length, it's jammed down on the surface.
Ebadot Hossain is off! He has now taken a tumble a couple of times and will need a bit of attention from the physio. Hope he is fine.
Flatter and on off, defended off the back foot.

Drags his length back and delivers it just outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite moves back and plays late. He guides it behind backward point and picks up three runs. Ebadot Hossain gives the chase and pulls it back. It seems he has hurt himself in the process and is going out for some treatment.
Once again it's flighted and outside off, it's defended off the front foot.
Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite lunges and defends it watchfully.
Mehidy Hasan (5-0-24-0) is back on.
Length ball outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to cover and gets a quick single.
On off and on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it towards mid off.
Touch fuller and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it towards the fielder at mid on.
On a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone towards the keeper.
On a good length and on middle, this is again defended towards the mid on region.
Lands it on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it to the mid on fielder.
A tad bit short and on middle, Bonner goes back inside the crease to work it onto the leg side. End of the over from Shakib Al Hasan and he is going off the field, maybe for a breather.
Shorter this time, around off. Bonner goes on the back foot but fails to cut it past point.
This one goes on with the arm! Quicker and flatter, sliding into middle and leg. Nkrumah Bonner does well to rock back and defend it out.
Floated up, close to the off pole. Bonner blocks it out on the off side.
Nicely bowled! A touch of flight, on a nagging length and outside off. Bonner caresses it towards cover-point.
Tossed up, full and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite whips it towards mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Back of a length and just outside off, Nkrumah Bonner leaves it alone towards the keeper.
