Outside off and on a good length, Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it.
Fuller and down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Goes fuller this time, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the mid off region.
Outside off again, Nkrumah Bonner guides it to point and rotates the strike.
Good-length delivery on off, Nkrumah Bonner eases it towards point.
Quicker delivery, angled in off a good length. Cramps Kraigg Brathwaite for space as he steps back and plays it staright.
Full once again and on off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite gets low and defends.
Back-of-a-length delivery on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite goes on his back foot and punches it back.
Full outside off, a firm defense from Kraigg Brathwaite.
Full and flighted once again. This one turns away and Kraigg Brathwaite plays it well.
Flighted on off stump. Defended back to the bowler.
Fuller in length and on off, Nkrumah Bonner blocks it solidly.
On middle and quicker too, Nkrumah Bonner defends it away.

Outside off and on a good length, Nkrumah Bonner looks to drive it but misses. A loud appeal for a caught behind but the finger stays down. The replay shows that the ball went past the outside edge, good decision not to review that one. The UltraEdge also backs the decision.
Good-length delivery just outside off, Nkrumah Bonner leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Nkrumah Bonner looks to block it but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls towards the left side of the keeper.
Bowls it on a good length and down the middle, Nkrumah Bonner defends it solidly.
Good-length delivery, angling in and keeping its line. Kraigg Brathwaite is watchful and plays it well.
Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length angled in once again, Kraigg Brathwaite works it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Good-length delivery is angled into the pads. Knocks it to mid-wicket.
Full and on the stumps, defended back down the pitch.
On a good length outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite gets a thickish outside edge to backward point.
FOUR! This was well-timed by Nkrumah Bonner. Fuller and on off, Nkrumah Bonner bends his knees and creams it past covers for a boundary.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Nkrumah Bonner defends it back towards Ebadot Hossain.
On a full length and on middle, Nkrumah Bonner blocks it away.
Touch fuller and on off, Nkrumah Bonner guides it towards the mid off fielder.
Outside off this time and on a good length, Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it.
Fuller in length and down the middle, Nkrumah Bonner guides it towards the fielder at point.
Shakib Al Hasan keeping it simple bowling full and stump to stump. Kraigg Brathwaite plays this one safely.
Full on off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite happy to defend this one.
Full on the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid on and rushes for a quick single. The mid-on fielder makes a meal of it and the misfield allows the batters to take two.
Full delivery on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends with a straight bat.

SAFE! Nkrumah Bonner has no idea what he is doing there but he survives. This is flatter and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it towards cover-point and looks for the single but decides against it. Bonner however is already halfway down the track. The fielder over there is just a tad slow in getting rid of the ball as Shakib Al Hasan whips off the bails. The decision does get sent upstairs but the replay shows that Bonner saved himself by putting in the desperate dive.
Is that run-out? A huge mix-up in the middle but Nkrumah Bonner seems to have made it. The decision is sent upstairs and the replay shows that the dive did save Bonner. NOT OUT!
Back-of-a-length on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite steps back and tries to pull it but mistimes it to mid off.
Length ball and wide outside off, Nkrumah Bonner lets it go towards the keeper.
Nkrumah Bonner is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Almost an unplayable delivery from Ebadot Hossain and Bangladesh have the second breakthrough. Hossain comes from round the wicket, and goes a bit wide of the crease. This is bowled full and angled into the middle stump line, the ball straightens after pitching as well. Raymon Reifer looks to play at it with an angled bat and ends up playing all around it as the outside edge is found. Nurul Hasan takes a sharp catch diving to his left and the salute celebration is out from Ebadot Hossain.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: Touch fuller and on middle, Raymon Reifer eases it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! On a length and down the leg side, Raymon Reifer uses the pace of the ball and just gives it a fine tickle. The ball races through the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Outside off again, Raymon Reifer doesn't bother at it.
On a good length and outside off, Raymon Reifer lets it go through and towards the keeper.
On a good length outside off, bowled slower in the air by Shakib Al Hasan. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards cover-point.
Straighter delivery on a good length. Defended back down the pitch.
FOUR! Delicately played! Touch short from Shakib Al Hasan outside off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite takes a step back and cuts it past backward point for a boundary in the wide third man region.

Shout for a caught behind! Didn't look out to the naked eye and maybe it was just a review taken out of desperation. Shakib Al Hasan flights it up nicely, around off. The ball grips and turns away sharply as Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend off the front foot. Brathwaite gets beaten past the outside edge. The keeper though seems absolutely certain that there is an outside edge on it and Shakib Al Hasan does take the review for a caught-behind decision. The third umpire checks UltraEdge and confirms there's no spike on it. Brathwaite survives and Bangladesh lose a review as well.
Good-length delivery outside off, Defended to short cover.
Shakib Al Hasan begins bowling short and wide, Kraigg Brathwaite goes on his back foot and works it to deep backward point for a brace.
A maiden from Ebadot Hossain. Outside off this time and fuller in length, Raymon Reifer defends it to the fielder at short covers.
Length ball and outside off, left alone by Raymon Reifer.
Much fuller this time, Raymon Reifer defends it towards the fielder at point.
Back of a length and wide outside off, Raymon Reifer lets it go through nad towards the keeper.
Bowls it on a good length and outside off, Raymon Reifer doesn't bother at it and lets it through.
On a length and down the middle, Raymon Reifer guides it towards the mid off fielder.

DRINKS! The first half of the final session on Day 1 has been quite fiercely contested but certainly, West Indies will be the happier of the two sides. They haven't been able to score freely by any means but have taken a significant chunk out of the Bangladeshi total without much fuss. Mustafizur Rahman has been probing and probing for the visitors and has picked up one wicket. Kraigg Brathwaite's stay at the crease is the key for West Indies and the visitors will be hoping to get rid of him at the earliest. Also, Ebadot Hossain (6-2-7-0) comes in to replace Mustafizur Rahman.
Bowls the same delivery once again and Kraigg Brathwaite repeats the defensive shot as well. Umpires call for refreshments!
Full and on off, defended solidly.
FOUR! Powered down the ground! Width offered outside off stump, full and slow. Kraigg Brathwaite uses muscle to thump this straight past mid on for a boundary.
Looped up, full and outside off. Defended towards short cover.
Full and on middle. Raymon Reifer knocks it to long on for a single.
Floated full outside off, defended to short mid off.
The skipper, Shakib Al Hasan brings himself back into the attack. He's bowled the single over so far which was a maiden.
Fuller and down on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it straight but the bowler stops it with his leg. Just a single from the over.
On a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend it but the ball hits his gloves and rolls towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge. The ball bounces back towards the bowler.
On off and on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the fielder at mid on.
On middle and much fuller in length, Raymon Reifer eases it towards point and takes a quick single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Raymon Reifer flicks it but straight towards the fielder at leg gully.
Slower delivery bowled short and in line with the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks and the ball just loops over him to the wicket-keeper.
On off stump once again but bowled back-of-a-length. Kraigg Brathwaite gets on his toes and defends it back to the bowler.
Back-of-a-length delivery, outside off, extra bounce off the wicket, Kraigg Brathwaite fends it to square leg.
Short and wide outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite can't make the most of it and mistimes his cut to point.
Good-length on off stump. Solid defense from Kraigg Brathwaite.

FOUR! Great timing on that shot! Full and angling into the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite uses his wrists and splits the gap between mid on and mid-wicket. The timing was so good that the ball kept running away to the boundary away from the chasing fielders.
On a length and on off, Raymon Reifer drives it straight towards the fielder at cover.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to the left of leg gully. A diving effort from Litton Das once again but it's a bit too far away from him. Single taken.

Oh, this was close. On a length and outside off, Raymon Reifer looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge. Excellent effort from Litton Das at second slip diving to his right but he can only get his fingertips on it. Maybe, just maybe, had he left it for Najmul Hossain Shanto at first slip, it could have carried. Single taken.
Fuller in length, on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it towards short fine leg for one.
Fuller and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to drive it but the ball hits the bottom part of his bat. The ball rolls towards the fielder at mid off.
On a good length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go towards the keeper.
Continues to bowl on a good length and around off. Raymon Reifer knocks it to extra cover.
Outside off stump on a good length. Raymon Reifer lets this go to the keeper.
FOUR! Smashes it down the ground! Full on off stump, Raymon Reifer takes a stride forward and hits it straight past mid off to get off the mark in style.
Good-length ball bowled on middle and leg. Raymon Reifer works it towards mid-wicket.

Appeal for a run out... SAFE! On a good length and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it towards covers and sets off for a quick single. The fielder over there gets in the direct hit at the bowler's end and there's an appeal for a run-out. The fielding side doesn't seem confident though and the third umpire confirms the same. The replay shows that Brathwaite had grounded his bat down in time. Just the single then.
Slightly full outside off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite plays it to short mid off.
Back of a length and down the leg side, Raymon Reifer gets in two minds but ducks down to leave it alone in the end.
Much fuller and on middle, Raymon Reifer eases it towards the fielder at silly mid on.
Length ball and just outside off, Raymon Reifer doesn't bother playing at it and lets it go.
Outside off this time, shaping it in, Raymon Reifer looks to block it but misses as the ball goes towards the keeper.
Fires it down the middle, Raymon Reifer defends it solidly.
Raymon Reifer is in at number 3.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Strange, strange dismissal but Mustafizur Rahman provides the much-needed breakthrough for Bangladesh. Mustafizur angles it in on a length and into the off stump from outside off. John Campbell puts a big stride forward and looks to defend it out with soft hands. The ball takes the bottom part of the blade and trickles behind to dislodge one of the bails as Campbell tries to keep it out. Campbell cannot believe it. Can this be the stroke of luck Bangladesh need to get going?
Commentary.Howout: b Mustafizur Rahman

Commentary.Commentary: Slower delivery, bowled full and in line with the stumps, Kraigg Brathwaite puts his bat down and plays it to short mid off.
Short and aimed for the body, Kraigg Brathwaite steps away and lets it through.
Full and wide outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to drive hard, stopped at short mid off.
Full again on middle and off. Defended straight back.
Misses out! A rank half-volley and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite punches it to mid off.
Back of a length outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite plays a loose shot, chasing the delivery. It misses the edge of the bat and goes through to the keeper.
Goes fuller and just outside off, John Campbell looks to play at it but gets beaten past the inside edge as the ball angles in a long way.
Outside off and fuller in length, John Campbell drives it straight towards the fielder at mid off.
On a good length and outside off, John Campbell leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Outside off this time, John Campbell pushes it towards covers and gets a couple of runs.
Fuller again on middle and leg, John Campbell flicks it towards the mid on region.
Starts with a fuller delivery on off, John Campbell drives it straight towards the fielder at cover.
Pace from both ends now as Mustafizur Rahman (5-4-1-0) is brought back into the attack as well.
Good-length delivery on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid on.
On a good length outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite knocks it to short mid off.
Straighter this time on a good length. Kraigg Brathwaite punches it straight past the bowler for a couple of runs down the ground.
Persists with the same line, slightly fuller. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves this one alone as well.
Good-length delivery, outside the off-stump channel, left alone by Kraigg Brathwaite.
Full and on the pads, Campbell works it towards the mid-wicket region and picks up a single.
Khaled Ahmed (5-3-3-0) is brought back into the attack.
On middle this time, John Campbell tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Touch fuller and down the middle, John Campbell leans forward and defends it to cover.
FOUR! On a length and outside off, John Campbell gets across, waits for the ball and slaps it past covers for a boundary.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, John Campbell defends it back towards the bowler.
SIX! This was effortless and beautifully timed. Fuller and around middle and leg, John Campbell smokes it over wide long on fence for a maximum.
On a good length, outside off. Brathwaite pushes it out towards cover-point.
Ebadot Hossain persisting with the outside off stump line on a good length. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves this one alone as well.
On a good length once again but straighter in line with the stumps. John Campbell works it to square leg for a single.
NO BALL! Good length from Ebadot Hossain as he pitches this outside off, John Campbell shoulders arms to it. Ebadot Hossain has overstepped and given away an extra run.
On a good length and angling into the batter. Pitches it wide from the off-stump line and is left alone by John Campbell.
Fuller this time outside the off stump. John Campbell gets his front foot forward and defends it firmly to cover.
Short ball outside off, John Campbell does not offer any shot.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it back towards Mehidy Hasan.
Touch fuller this time, quicker too, Kraigg Brathwaite goes on his back foot and defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg.
Much fuller with a hint of turn, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it away.
Fuller in length and on leg, John Campbell nudges it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to mid on and takes a single.
Good-length down leg side. Well stopped by Nurul Hasan behind the wicket diving to his right.

LBW SHOUT! Ebadot Hossain angles this one into the batter's pads, John Campbell looks to work it leg side but falls over and gets pinged on the pads. Huge appeal, especially from the keeper but the umpire remains unmoved. They think about the review but Shakib opts against it. On replay, we can see that it would have been the umpire's call on hitting the wickets.
Ebadot Hossain goes short angled into the body. John Campbell ducks under this one.
Good-length delivery outside off, driven to cover.
Corrects his length and goes full on off stump, John Campbell knocks it to mid on.
Ebadot Hossain begins with a short delivery bowled wide outside off, John Campbell slashes it to deep point for a brace.
A slight delay as the physio comes out and uses the magic spray on the right arm of one of the umpires, Joel Wilson.
Fuller in length and down the middle stump line, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to backward square leg for a brace.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again blocked back towards Mehidy Hasan.
On middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to the mid-wicket region.
Outside off again and fuller in length, John Campbell drives it to long off and takes a single.
Fuller and on off giving it some air, John Campbell guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
Wide delivery on a length. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.
Good-length delivery bowled on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends this back to the bowler.
Low full toss on the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite digs it out firmly.
On a good length but wide of the off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves this one alone.
Back-of-a-length delivery, John Campbell gets enough width to tap it towards backward point for a single.
On a good length outside off, John Campbell raises his arms and lets it go.
Ebadot Hossain (3-2-2-0) to continue from the opposite end.
Bowls it outside off this time, Campbell cuts it to the fielder at point. A quick single is taken. This is good running between the wickets.
Tossed up delivery, John Campbell defends it solidly.
On middle and fuller in length, John Campbell lofts it without much timing and just manages to clear mid off. The fielder chases it down and a couple of runs are taken.
Tossed up outside off, John Campbell guides it to gully.
Outside off and short, John Campbell cuts it but straight towards the fielder at point.
Tossed up on off, John Campbell eases it to short cover.

Right then, the players and the umpires are back on the field. The West Indian openers, Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell are set to resume their innings. It will be Mehidy Hasan to continue with his off-spin bowling after the break.

Welcome back to our coverage of the final session of Day 1 of the first Test match between West Indies and Bangladesh. The hosts will be looking to build on the platform laid down by the openers who have negotiated the new ball well. Bangladesh on the other hand will want to restrict West Indies in their first innings to a low total. They did bowl 10 maiden overs in the first 15 overs but they need wickets now. Let us resume witnessing this engrossing battle between bat and ball!
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Another session belonged to West Indies! They took very little time to pick the remaining four wickets and folded out Bangladesh for a paltry total. Had it not been for a counter-attacking half-century by the newly elected captain Shakib Al Hasan, the touring team would have struggled to touch even 100. In reply, the West Indian openers started very watchfully and have managed to preserve all their wickets. Kraigg Brathwaite did offer them a chance but Mominul Haque dropped the catch. Post that, it was all about the hosts putting up a strong defensive display. The bowlers have dominated thus far. Bangladesh didn't get any wickets but bowled very tidily. Do join us at 12.30 am local (7 pm GMT, previous day) to see whether the bat can dominate the ball in the final session of Day 1.
Back of a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone towards the keeper. That will be Tea on Day 1.
Touch fuller this time, Brathwaite defends it out solidly.
Good-length delivery outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to play at it but gets an outside edge. The ball rolls towards the slip.
Slightly shorter angling into the batter, Kraigg Brathwaite hops a bit and blocks it away.
Bowls it outside off this time, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
On a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it towards short cover and straight to the fielder.
Mehidy Hasan switches to around the wicket and floats it up around middle and leg. John Campbell defends it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Brathwaite backs away and taps it towards the cover region for a quick single. Good running.
Flatter delivery, on middle, Brathwaite keeps it out.
Brathwaite looks to use his feet now but Hasan sees him coming. Hasan pulls back the length and angles it into the pads, Brathwaite defends it out.

FOUR! First sign of aggression from Brathwaite and he picks up a boundary, the first of the innings. Darted in on leg stump, Brathwaite gets low and slogs it into the vacant square leg region for a boundary.
Uppish but safe! Mehidy Hasan starts off with a speared-in delivery on the pads, Brathwaite flicks it just past short leg and towards square leg.
Mehidy Hasan is ready to bowl now after just one over from Shakib Al Hasan. Maybe, he wants a change of ends.
Good-length delivery just outside off, Campbell tries to block it but misses. The ball just aired past his blade and goes into the gloves of the keeper.
On a length and on middle, Campbell defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off, John Campbell looks to slap it but misses.
Good-length delivery on middle, John Campbell defends it out. The ball bounces back near the stumps and he blocks it with his leg.
On middle this time and on a length, John Campbell defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes 'round the wicket. Bowls it on a length and outside off, John Campbell looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge. The ball bounces back towards the keeper.
Quicker and flatter, darted into middle. Brathwaite blocks it out. Shakib Al Hasan starts off with a maiden.
Tossed up this time, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to drive it through covers but mistimes it towards silly mid off.
Nicely flighted and angled into middle, Brathwaite watches it well and keeps it out.
A bit quicker through the air and on off, Brathwaite strides out to defend.
Floated up on off stump, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Starts off with an in-drifter on middle and leg, Brathwaite nudges it out on the leg side.
Shakib Al Hasan brings himself into the attack.
Back-of-a-length delivery, Brathwaite guides it towards covers and rotates the strike.
A brilliant inswinger. Fuller in length following the batter, Brathwaite blocks it out solidly. Oh, it's a no ball. A late call from the umpire and he has recalled the bowler to bowl the final ball.
Good-length delivery wide outside off, Brathwaite lets it go through and towards the keeper.
Ebadot Hossain keeps bowling it on a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite doesn't bother at it and lets it go towards the keeper.
Similar to the last delivery, Kraigg Brathwaite again leaves it through and towards the keeper.
On a good length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms at it.
Starts with a fuller one on off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend it but gets a thick inside edge. The ball rolls towards the short mid-wicket region.
On off, Campbell pats it towards mid on.
Around off, Campbell leaves it alone this time.

Just short! Khaled Ahmed bowls it around the top of off and the ball just nips back in ever so slightly. John Campbell has a poke at it with soft hands but gets an outside edge that lands in front of the man at second slip.
Pitched up, outside off and this one shapes away a fair bit after passing the batter. John Campbell offers no shot.
In that channel outside off, Campbell lets it through to the keeper.
Length, around off, Brathwaite pushes at it off the front foot and picks up a single towards cover-point.
Length ball, on off. Campbell defends it off the front foot.
Short of a length and around off, Campbell looks to cut from too close to the body but edges it back onto the deck.
Some issues with the landing area. Mustafizur Rahman is not happy, maybe some loose soil there. The groundsmen have been asked to fix the issue.

Mustafizur Rahman pulls back the length and tries to attack the pads but spills it down the leg side. Campbell fails to get any bat on it. Also, the Fizz slips while in his stride and is a bit concerned with the landing area.
Full, on off and shaping away. John Campbell keeps it out on the off side.
In the gap! Good-length ball, around the hips. Brathwaite plays at it with soft hands and keeps it down towards the vacant short leg region. Brathwaite picks up a single.
This is on a fuller length and slanted well across the right-hander. Brathwaite leaves it alone.
The maidens keep on coming, still just the one over scored off by West Indies. A length ball, angled in around off. John Campbell pushes it out towards the cover region.
On the fifth stump line and quite full, Campbell isn't interested in playing at it.
On a nagging length, nipping back in a bit from outside off. Campbell shoulders arms.
Full and around off, stroked away towards cover-point.
Probing line. Khaled Ahmed gets a bit more pace behind this one and angles it in sharply into the off stump. Solidly defended out though by Campbell.
Full and around off, shaping away a bit. Easy leave for John Campbell.

Well bowled and well left as well. Mustafizur Rahman just pulls back the length a touch and bowls it really close to the off stump. Brathwaite reads the line of the ball well and makes the leave. Maiden!
Gets it a bit closer to the off pole now and keeps it full. Brathwaite lets it through to the keeper once again.
This is full but angled well across the batter, no need to play at that.
Just a shade fuller and on off, Brathwaite plays it late and defends it towards short cover.
Good-length delivery, around the top of off. Brathwaite defends it out onto the leg side.

Half an appeal from the bowler but probably going down leg. This is served on a length, around middle and leg and the ball shapes back into the right-hander. Brathwaite looks to tuck it away but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Quick single now and Kraigg Brathwaite too is off the mark! Length ball, on middle, Brathwaite plays it with soft hands in front of square on the leg side and scampers through for a run.
Fuller and bowled with good pace, close to the off pole. Brathwaite makes an assured leave.
Length this time, around middle. Brathwaite nudges it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR LEG BYES! Khaled Ahmed errs in line and gives away a few runs. Very full and angled in on the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads and runs away past the keeper into the fine leg fence.

John Campbell and West Indies are finally underway! It has taken them 32 balls but the Windies have their first run on the board. This is dug in a bit short and angled at the body. Campbell pulls it past square leg and collects a single.
Ahmed angles it in around the top of off, Campbell hangs on the back foot and keeps it out around the point region.
Fuller and on off, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out. Five overs done, West Indies are yet to open their account.
Good lines, around off and making the batter life. Kraigg defends it back.
Fullish and close to off, shaping in, Kraigg defends it from the inner half of his blade to mid-wicket.
Mustafizur Rahman receives his first official warning for running on the danger area. He has to be a bit careful now.
Outside off, left alone with ease.
Angles a full ball around off, a hint of swing, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with soft hands.
Bowls it full and around off, Kraigg covers the line and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, on off, Campbell flicks but finds the fielder in front of square on the leg side. Make it four maidens in a row.
Short and outside off, John lets it be.

Huge shout for an lbw, not given. Too high. Back of a length, around off and angling in, John Campbell walks across and tries to pull but misses. He is hit on the thigh pad, they appeal but unsuccessfully.
Very full and on middle, Campbell flicks it across the line but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Probing delivery. This one is on a length and outside off, John Campbell is forward in defense but gets a soft outside edge. It falls in front of the slip cordon.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave for John Campbell.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to square leg. Three consecutive maidens to start this innings.
On a good length and outside off, left alone.
Rare bad shot attempted. Full and wide outside off, Kraigg goes chasing after it but fails to connect.

PUT DOWN! The leg gully fielder was there for this very reason but fails to do the job. Mustafizur Rahman pitches it around middle, on a length and gets it to shape in. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and files quickly to Mominul Haque who fails to hang on to the catch. That's a big miss, we all know Kraigg Brathwaite's appetite for big runs.
Around off, on a length, blocked from the back foot.

Uppish but safe! Movement and extra bounce from around middle, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend but it takes the shoulder of his bat and flies to square leg. It falls away from the fielder stationed there.

Appeal for an lbw! Nothing from the umpire, and no DRS taken either. Fuller and on middle, angling down, John Campbell tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to the fielder on the leg side. Missing leg, easily.
Back of a length, on off, John covers the line and blocks it to mid on.
Fuller in length and outside off, on a driving length, John Campbell allows it through to the keeper.
Sharp pace again, full and skidding down the leg side, John attempts to flick but misses.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Campbell tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Sharp delivery first up from Khaled Ahmed. He is operating from 'round the wicket with the wind. Angles it in around off, skidding off the surface, John Campbell defends it from the back foot.
Khaled Ahmed to operate from the other end.
A touch short on this occasion, around off, Kraigg is on the back foot as he blocks it to the off side.
Pitches it up and close to off, shaping in a bit, Kraigg Brathwaite is on the front foot as he defends it down.
On a good length, around middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it from the back foot to the leg side.
This one is angled away from the batter, outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite allows it through to the keeper.
Again it's an excellent delivery. Mustafizur Rahman serves it around middle and leg, getting it to move back in, Kraigg Brathwaite shuffles back and defends it in front of his pads.
Starts well. Lands a full ball around off, a hint of inward shape, Kraigg Brathwaite is half-forward as he defends.

We are back for the chase! A minimum of 17 overs left in the day's play and if West Indies do get close to the target, then play might be prolonged. The umpires and the players are back on the field. Kraigg Brathwaite and John Campbell are the openers for West Indies. Mustafizur Rahman has the new ball in hand and is raring to go. Let's play...
... THE RUN CHASE ...

What a turnaround it has been since the second new ball was taken! Shakib Al Hasan and Nurul Hasan started off quickly after the Tea break as Nurul too surpassed the fifty-run mark. But once Kemar Roach had the new cherry in hand, he was unstoppable. The skipper and Nurul, both got out playing loose shots and after that, the tailenders had no answer to Roach's prowess with the new ball. Roach ended up with his 10th five-wicket haul in Test cricket and Alzarri Joseph picked up three wickets as well. The target for West Indies is a fairly simple one, 84 runs to get and take a 1-0 lead in the series. Will they be able to do so before the end of play on Day 3 itself? Find out soon as the chase is coming up next.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Kemar Roach with a sensational five-wicket haul and he has bundled out the opposition in a hurry here. This is on a length, nipping back in from around off and this one stays low. Ebadot Hossain looks to defend but is undone by the lack of bounce and the ball castles into the middle stump. Roach picks up his 50th wicket at this venue and also goes on level with Michael Holding with 249 Test wickets. Bangladesh have been bundled out for 245!
Commentary.Howout: b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Joshua Da Silva is certain that there is bat involved and lets out a strong appeal but the umpire remains unmoved. This is a good bouncer, banged in over middle. Ebadot Hossain tries to awkwardly fend it off but the ball seems to have just gone over his bat. There might have been a glove involved but West Indies have no review remaining.
This is banged in short but outside off. Ebadot Hossain plays inside the line of the ball.
Attempted yorker this time, around off. Ebadot Hossain jams it out towards short cover.
Starts off with a shortish delivery over middle. Ebadot Hossain gets nicely behind the line and makes the block.
Alzarri Joseph attempts a yorker but gets it wide from off stump. Khaled Ahmed plays it towards covers.
Good-length delivery angled into the pads. Khaled Ahmed somehow manages to fend it down towards short leg.
Alzarri Joseph pulls the length back a bit and bowls an outswinger outside off stump. Khaled Ahmed tries to play at it and gets beaten.
Full on middle, Khaled Ahmed blocks this awkwardly.
Full and outside off, Khaled Ahmed just keeps his bat in front of his pads and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Khaled Ahmed is the last man in for Bangladesh.

OUT! Cleaned him up! Alzarri Joseph knocks over Mustafizur Rahman and West Indies are now one wicket away from bundling out Bangladesh for the second time in this Test match. Joseph comes from around the wicket and angles it in from around off. The ball goes on with the angle as Mustafizur Rahman tries to swing across the line. Rahman misses and the ball goes on to hit the top of leg stump. Joseph picks up his third wicket and Bangladesh currently lead by 83 runs.
Commentary.Howout: b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Beaten! This is angled in on a length from outside off. The ball straightens after pitching and goes past the outside edge of Ebadot Hossain's willow.
Back of a length, outside off. Mustafizur Rahman is able to guide it past point and collects a single.
Very full and outside off, shaping away a touch. Mustafizur Rahman makes room looking to go over cover but misses.
Full and wide, Mustafizur Rahman has a go at this one as well but fails to connect.
Good length, over middle. Mustafizur Rahman backs away looking to cut but is beaten for pace.

SIX! Mustafizur Rahman chances his arm and gets maximum purchase! A length ball, around the top of off. Mustafizur Rahman just goes hard after it and gets a top edge that flies all the way over the third man fence for a maximum.
Full and angling into the pads. Ebadot Hossain gets his bat down in time and knocks it to mid-wicket.
Fuller this time on middle, Ebadot Hossain blocks this back to the bowler.
Similar delivery slighlty closer to Ebadot Hossain who is unsure whether to play or leave it alone. Goes through to the keeper.
Alzarri Joseph goes back to bowling outside off on a good length. Ebadot Hossain leaves this one as well.
Alzarri Joseph goes full on off, Ebadot Hossain fends it awkwardly towards point.
On a good length outside off, Ebadot Hossain raises his arms and lets it go.
Full again and at the stumps, Mustafizur Rahman backs away and keeps it out on the off side.
On a fuller length and angled into leg stump. Mustafizur Rahman keeps it out.
Dead ball signaled by the umpire! Full and on the pads, Mustafizur Rahman offers no shot but the ball deflects off the pads and races away into the fine leg fence. The runs won't count though.
Mustafizur Rahman is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A loose shot from Nurul Hasan and both the set batters have now been sent back to the pavilion. Back of a length from Kemar Roach this time and well outside off. Nurul Hasan goes chasing after a wide one and looks to slap it through the line but the ball takes the outside edge and Joshua Da Silva takes a simple catch behind the sticks. Roach picks up his fourth wicket as Bangladesh lead by 76 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: On a length and attacking the stumps, Nurul Hasan goes back and across to work it on the leg side.
In the air but in the gap as well. This is floated up on the pads, Ebadot Hossain with an uppish defensive prod and the ball goes past the man at mid-wicket for a single.
Full this time on off and middle, Nurul Hasan defends this back to the bowler.

FOUR! Nurul Hasan comes up with his own helicopter shot! Alzarri Joseph bowls this full and outside off, Nurul Hasan thumps it through covers and his arms swing all the way around his head. Stands and admires his shot.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off stump. Nurul Hasan gets on his back foot and punches it to covers.
Full outswinger just outside off, Nurul Hasan knocks it to short mid on.
Brings the line closer on a good length, Nurul Hasan is beaten this time as he hangs his bat down.
Wonderful shape away first-up from Alzarri Joseph. On a good length outside off, goes through to the keeper.
Alzarri Joseph comes in to replace Jayden Seales.
Another maiden over for Kemar Roach but he hardly troubled the batter. Full again, outside off and shaping away. Ebadot Hossain plays inside the line of the ball.
Full again but angling down leg this time. Good take from Joshua Da Silva down to his left.
And again! Full and wide outside off, Ebadot Hossain doesn't play at it.
Full and wide, shaping away. No need to play at that one.
This is a bit fuller in length and wide of the off stump. Ebadot Hossain watches as the ball goes through to the keeper.
On a good length, angling it into the off stump. Ebadot Hossain makes a solid block off the front foot.
Full again and around the fifth stump line, keeps on shaping it away. Nurul Hasan plays inside the line of the ball.
Full and around off, moving away from the right-hander, Nurul lets it through to the keeper.
Better from Seales. This is a bit closer to the off pole, good length and shaping away. Nurul Hasan plays and misses.
WIDE! Jayden Seales has sprayed this one way beyond the tramline outside off and the ball moves away as well. A wide is called.
thrice in a row now from Jayden Seales but he needs to get a bit closer to the off pole. Nurul Hasan once again plays inside the line of the ball.
And again! Angling it in from outside off but the ball shapes away. Just a bit too wide to induce the outside edge.
On a length, outside off and shaping away from the right-hander. Nurul Hasan plays inside the line of the ball.

Kemar Roach looks for the dream ball as he tries to swing it away from middle and leg stump but the ball just goes on with the angle and down leg. Ebadot Hossain looks to tickle it away but misses. A wicket-maiden then for Kemar Roach!
Length again, a bit wider of the off stump. Ebadot Hossain leaves it alone.
Around the top of off, Ebadot gets behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Kemar Roach seems to be in the groove now. This is a bit fuller and angling in a long way from outside off. Hossain makes the leave but the ball goes just past the off stump.
Goes fuller and wider, Ebadot Hossain lets it through to the keeper.
Ebadot Hossain is the new man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally, West Indies have a breakthrough. Straight to Kraigg Brathwaite and Shakib Al Hasan cannot believe it! Kemar Roach comes from around the wicket and serves a length ball around off. The ball moves away a bit and there is some extra zip off the pitch. Shakib goes hard at it and punches it uppishly towards short cover where Brathwaite pouches the ball around his head. A top knock from Shakib comes to an end and Roach is absolutely elated. The 123-run stand is broken and Bangladesh are effectively 70 for 7.
Commentary.Howout: c Kraigg Brathwaite b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Closer this time but not close enough. Fuller and just outside off, nipping away, Nurul tries to defend but doesn't goes chasing for the ball.
Quite wide outside off, an easy leave. Jayden Seales needs to get closer to the stumps.
Serves it on a length and outside off, curling away off the seam, Nurul again lets it be.
Another outswinger outside off, Nurul keeps his bat close to his body and allows it through to the keeper.
Outswinger, on a length and outside off, Nurul pushes inside the line and misses.
Around off, on a length and seaming into the left-hander from 'round the wicket angle, Shakib clips it behind square leg for a run.
Jayden Seales to share the second new ball with Kemar Roach.
Lands it on a length, around off, Hasan defends it off his back foot.
Full and swinging in the air, around off, Nurul gets forward and defends it to point.
Back of a length, around off, defended down from the back foot.

FOUR! Jayden Seales should have done better near the fence. Full and around leg, Nurul Hasan flicks it aerially behind square leg. It races away and beats the sliding effort of the fielder for a boundary.
Wide! Wayward delivery, short and way wide outside off. The batter leaves and it's a late call for a wide by umpire Joel Wilson.
A hint of shape again, outside off, Nurul tries to drive but misses.
Beats the bat! Big lateral movement. On a length and outside off, shaping in, Nurul pushes at it and misses.

The second new ball is now available. As expected, Kraigg Brathwaite has opted to take it straight away. Can West Indies replicate what Bangladesh did with the second new ball on Day 2? It will be Kemar Roach (19-8-40-2) who will have the first bite at the cherry.

SAFE! Fuller in length and outside off, Shakib drives it back off the inner half. The bowler tries to stop but perhaps only gets a fingertip. It goes on to hit the stumps at the other end. Nurul is outside the crease and they appeal. The umpire refers it upstairs and the replays find that there is no touch from the bowler.

Is that a run-out? Half an appeal from the West Indies players as the ball goes past Raymon Reifer and crashes into the stumps. The decision is sent upstairs and the replay shows that Reifer's fingers weren't close to the ball.
Around off, on a length, Shakib defends it near his front pad.
FOUR! Short in length and wide outside off, Shakib reaches out for it and guides it behind backward point for a boundary.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, it's tucked to deep square leg for one.
Lands it on a length, around off, it's pushed from the back foot to cover-point.
FOUR! Fuller in length and angling down the leg side, Nurul tries to flick but gets a faint tickle. It races away to fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted and around middle, Shakib works it wide of square leg for a single.
Flatter and around off, defended off the back foot.
Slower through the air, full and around off, it's eased away to long off for a single.
Loopy and full, around off, Nurul is forward as he defends it to covers.
Short and wide outside off, cut to point.
Spinning down the leg side, Shakib tickles it down to fine leg for a run.

Nurul Hasan seems to be struggling with an injury to the index finger on his right hand. There is already some taping on but since the last couple of deliveries, Nurul seems to be in a bit of pain. The physio is out and is just putting on some magic spraying and re-taping the finger. Nurul is all good to continue now.
Nearly a yorker, on middle, Nurul digs it out back towards the bowler. Maiden.
Slightly short and on off, Nurul punches it from the back foot to covers.
On a length, around middle and leg, Nurul covers the angle and defends it down.
Fullish and around middle, Nurul flicks it towards short mid-wicket. It goes on one bounce to the close-in fielder.
Targets the stumps and delivers it on a length, Nurul blocks it again from the front foot.
Full and angling in from around off, Nurul defends it off the front foot.
Raymon Reifer to continue from the opposite end.
Fuller and around middle, defended back off the front foot.
Tossed up, around middle, Shakib tries to flick but misses. It takes his pads and lobs near the vacant short leg region.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Full and flighted, outside off, Shakib drives it aerially towards mid off where Roach dives across to his right, stretches his one hand but it doesn't stick and goes behind for a boundary. Could have gone with both hands. The lead crosses 50.
FIFTY FOR NURUL! A timely knock from the wicketkeeper-batter. Flighted and around leg, Nurul tucks it to square leg for a run.
A bit short and close to off, Nurul cuts late but still finds the point fielder.
Flighted and around off, Nurul is on the back foot as he defends it back to the bowler.

The start of the final session on Day 3 has been delayed a bit. There was a slight drizzle as the players went into the Tea break and the square was quickly covered. The drizzle has stopped and the covers are off as well. The play should start in a few minutes time. Scratch that, the umpires are making their way back into the middle and so are the players. Shakib Al Hasan and Nurul Hasan are set to resume their stay at the crease. With the second new ball not far away, it will be interesting to see how the batters approach their innings. It will be Gudakesh Motie to start off with the ball after the break.
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

West Indies will be a bit disappointed with their bowling in the second session. The pitch has certainly eased out for the batters but with just one wicket needed to expose the opposition tail, they found it difficult to create opportunities. There have been a few edges and a couple of shouts for LBW but that has been it. The hosts will now look to shrug off the session gone by and get back into their strides after the break. The second new ball that is due in a few overs could be the key for West Indies. Can Bangladesh continue to score at a good rate without losing wickets? Or will West Indies be able to regain the lost momentum? Find out in the final session that starts at 12.30 am IST (7 pm GMT, the previous day).

Session summary - 27 overs, 95 runs and no wickets lost! What a wonderful session this has been for Bangladesh with the bat. They looked to be down and out at the Lunch interval but an unbeaten stand of 101 runs between skipper Shakib Al Hasan and Nurul Hasan has just about kept them in the game. The pair scored at a good rate and after getting rid of the deficit, the duo has put the visitors ahead by 48 runs. Their job is not done yet as a slight lapse in concentration here and all the hard work will be undone. But for now, they can breathe a bit easy.
Back of a length, outside off, Shakib stays on the back foot and punches it to mid off. That will be Tea on Day 3.
Short in length, around off, Nurul turns and pulls it down to fine leg for a run. Last ball before Tea coming up...
Angles it in, on a length around off, Nurul takes a step down the track and defends it to the off side.
Fuller in length around off, Nurul walks forward and defends it to mid on.
CENTURY STAND! Short in length and wide outside off, Shakib cuts it to deep point for a run. This stand has revived some hope in the Bangladesh camp. Lead is 47.
Lapse in concentration. Short in length and outside off, Shakib tries to punch it down but it beats the outside edge.
Loopy and full around off, Nurul eases it to the right of mid on and charges forward for a run. This time Shakib sends him back.
Flatter and shorter, around off, Shakib stays back and taps it down to point for a run.
Tossed up, around off, Shakib walks forward and brings his bat and pad together in defense.
Shakib Al Hasan seems to be struggling a bit out there. Shakib might have just stretched the hamstring a bit and is in a bit of pain but he will continue for now. Hope, all is fine.
A low full toss on middle, Hasan knocks it down to mid on and rushes across for a sharp single.
FOUR! Fine shot! Short in length, around off, Nurul immediately drops his weight on the back leg and powers it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Turning back in from around off, Shakin helps it to square leg and picks up a run.

FOUR! Slapped away! Short in length and outside off, Nurul Hasan latches onto it and slaps it through point. Good batting. The keeper had come up to the stumps and Nurul used the depth of the crease to create room.
On a length and around off, Nurul walks forward and blocks it down.
Fuller in length, around off and skidding off the seam, Nurul fails to defend and is hit on the back pad. A muted appeal for an lbw but it's going down the leg side.
Switches to 'round the wicket and serves a length ball down the leg side. Nurul tries to flick but misses. Joshua Da Silva fumbles but no run is taken.
FIFTY FOR SHAKIB! Second in this match for the skipper. Three in a row in Tests. On a good length and outside off, Shakib punches it through covers for a run. Bangladesh lead by 35 runs.
A length ball around off, Shakib walks forward and across before tapping it down to covers.
Flighted and full, wide outside off, Hasan offers no shot.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
Turning away from the batter, on the shorter side, Nurul cuts but finds the point fielder.
Quicker around off, steered through point for a single.
Walks forward to a full ball around off and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and around off, Shakib defends it off the front foot.

Another shout for an lbw! Not given. West Indies can't review now. A length ball, around leg, Nurul walks forward and tries to defend but misses. He is again hit on the back pad but the umpire shakes his head. The batter had come too far down the track anyway.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On a length, around middle, it's defended off the front foot.

Shout for an lbw, the finger has stayed down. Has it pitched outside leg? That's the only question, the rest seems fine in favour of the bowler. West Indies opt for the review. Around leg, on a length and skidding off the surface. Nurul Hasan fails to defend off the back foot and is pinged on the back pad. The UltraEdge finds nothing and the Ball Tracking shows that it has PITCHED OUTSIDE LEG, marginally! Review lost for West Indies, they have none left now.
Fuller in length and outside off, Shakib drives it to short cover where the fielder dives and deflects it towards mid off. They cross for a run.
Starts his spell by landing a length ball around off, Shakib gets on the front foot and pushes it to covers.
A surprise change in the bowling in the form of Raymon Reifer. Can he conjure up some magic and get a breakthrough for his side?
Skips down the track to a full ball and drives it to deepish mid off for a single. Lead moves to 32. Anything over 100 and West Indies will start to worry.
Flighted and full, around middle, Nurul works it in front of square leg for a run.
Quicker and flatter, around off, Nurul defends it from the back foot.
Floated and full, around middle, Hasan leans forward and defends it watchfully.
Turning down the leg side, it's nudged down to fine leg for a run.
Short in length, wide outside off, Nurul goes back and cuts it to deep cover for a run. This now is the highest partnership of this Test match.
Fraction short, around middle and leg, Shakib turns and glances it across the line. It goes on one bounce to leg gully. End of a fiery over from Alzarri Joseph!
Back of a length, on off, Shakib is on the back foot as he defends it to the leg side.
Shakib is bombarded with bouncers at the moment. He is not taking them on at the moment after taking a blow on the helmet. Safely ducked.
Joseph shows no mercy. Hurls across another bouncer, around middle and leg, Shakib ducks safely.

A slight halt in play! Shakib Al Hasan is hit flush on the helmet and the physio rushes out for a mandatory concussion check. There was some genuine pace behind it and Shakib looks a bit rattled. Hopefully, he is fine. Shakib gives the thumbs up and is good to continue.

Bang on the helmet! Another bouncer from Joseph, well-directed at the batter. Shakib tries to pull but misses. It goes past his gloves, pings him on the helmet and goes straight into the hands of Bonner at short leg. A stifled appeal for a catch but nothing doing. No bat, no gloves, only helmet.
Digs it in short, around off, Shakib turns inside the crease and pulls it to square leg. Finds the fielder.
Full and around off, Shakib Al Hasan drives it down to long on for a run.
Around middle, this is wristed away through mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Nurul Hasan creams it but straight to the man at extra cover.
Flatter and on off, blocked out by Nurul Hasan.
Flighted, around off and turning away. Nurul doesn't play at it.
Tossed up, on middle. Nurul Hasan gets a good stride forward and defends it out.
Bowls on a good length this time, on off stump, Shakib Al Hasan defends it straight back.
Alzarri Joseph is getting his bouncers right. Similar delivery attacking the batter. Shakib Al Hasan ducks under this one as well.
Better line this time, Short ball angled into the body. Shakib Al Hasan has to duck under this one.
Alzarri Joseph puts this one wide down leg stump. Continues to bowl short but Shakib Al Hasan does not need to play at it.
Around the wicket to the right-hander as well. Short and on leg. Nurul Hasan gets up and pulls it to backward square leg for a single.
Alzarri Joseph goes short on middle, Shakib Al Hasan gets a single to deep square leg.
Gudakesh Motie fires it in this time, full and on leg stump. Nurul Hasan jams it out on the leg side.
Flatter this time, around off. Nurul punches it out towards cover.
A hint of turn on this occasion. This is looped up around off stump and turns away after pitching. Nurul Hasan watches it well and lets it through to the keeper.
On off, pushed towards the left of the bowler.
Nicely flighted, full and on off. Nurul Hasan strokes it towards short cover.
On a length and around off, pushed towards cover-point.
Back-of-a-length delivery on leg stump. Nurul Hasan gets on his toes and glances towards fine leg for a single.
Alzarri Joseph adjust his length and goes a little fuller outside off. Defended towards cover.

Trying to be a bit too cheeky there Nurul Hasan. This is on a length and angled into leg stump. Nurul looks to make room and come down the pitch but has to check his drive. The ball goes off the pad and the keeper pouches it. There is a slight appeal for caught behind but the umpire remains unmoved. The replay shows that it was all pad and there was no inside edge on it.
FOUR! Well controlled by Nurul Hasan! Short again angled into leg, Nurul Hasan steps away from the stumps and uses the angle to pull it backward of square leg for a boundary!
On a good length pitching on middle. Defends it towards short leg.
Alzarri Joseph bangs this in short angled into the batter. Shakib Al Hasan swings his bat and pulls it wide of fine leg for a single.
Quicker and flatter, around off. This is played towards cover.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Aerial but a safe shot from Nurul Hasan. Tossed up on middle, Nurul just lifts it high and clears mid on with ease as the ball trickles away into the fence.
On a length and angled into the pads, this one keeps a shade low but Nurul manages to keep it out.
Tossed up on middle, Nurul blocks it out.
Flatter and around off, tapped away onto the off side for a quick single.
A length ball, around off. Nurul Hasan taps it towards cover-point.
Around the top of off, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
full and straight, this is clipped past square leg for a single.
Slightly short and outside off stump. Shakib Al Hasan slashes he ball past gully for two runs.
Alzarri Joseph continues bowling on a good length outside off. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it back down the pitch.
Good-length delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to mid-wicket.
Around the off stump, Shakib plays it late and opens the face of the bat to guide it down to third man for one.
Floated up on leg stump, Nurul flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Cut away nicely! Short and on off, Nurul Hasan rocks back and thumps it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, with a hint of flight and around off. Nurul defends it out.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
Starts off with a flatter delivery, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan waits for it and cuts it really late past backward point for a run.

DRINKS! It has been a remarkable first hour from Bangladesh with the bat post-Lunch. Shakib Al Hasan has been aggressive and Nurul Hasan too has played his shots. The pair has scored freely and with the pitch offering very little assistance now, the West Indies bowlers have had to toil a bit.  Bangladesh lead by 3 runs and their next agenda will be to get through Tea unscathed. West Indies need to pull up their socks if they are to bundle out the visitors soon. Also, Gudakesh Motie is brought back into the attack.
FOUR! Hammered away and West Indies will have to bat again! Short of a length and well outside off. Nurul Hasan stands tall and slaps it through the cover region for a boundary.
Jayden Seales bowling good length here and sticking to the offside line, Nurul Hasan leaves this one alone.
Jayden Seales continues bowling the same delivery. Nurul Hasan gets better contact this time and knocks it to covers.
Back to bowling good length and outside off, Nurul Hasan defends but gets an inside edge to square leg.

Risky shot from Shakib Al Hasan! Fuller this time outside off, Shakib Al Hasan gives it a charge and swings his arms. Mistimes the ball into the air over cover-point as it lands in no man's land. A single is taken.
Jayden Seales continues around the wicket to the left-hander. On-a-good-length delivery outside off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to short cover.

FOUR! Put away with ease by Nurul Hasan and the fifty partnership is up between these two. This is a half-volley around off, Nurul creams it through extra cover for a boundary. The West Indies is now almost wiped off.
Easy single on offer. Good length, around off. Shakib Al Hasan hops and dabs it down towards cover-point for a quick single. Bangladesh trail by just 6 runs now.
short of a length this time and on off. Nurul turns it past square leg and picks up a single.
On a good length, jagging back in from outside off. Nurul Hasan pushes it out towards the bowler.
Length ball, on the fifth stump line. Nurul Hasan taps it towards cover.
Starts off with a short ball, on leg stump. Shakib Al Hasan half-pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one.
Alzarri Joseph is now back into the attack.
Jayden Seales bowls short but the ball does not rise much after hitting the pitch. Nurul Hasan gets back and punches it towards the cover fielder.
Good-length delivery on off stump, Nurul Hasan defends it well this time.
Fuller outside off, Nurul Hasan puts his leg forward and leaves it late. The ball goes close to the stumps on its way to the keeper.
Short again this time and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan spins on his heels and pulls it to deep square leg for a single. No real timing in that shot.
Full and on off stump. Shakib Al Hasan defends it towards covers.
Good short delivery from Jayden Seales attacking the body of Shakib Al Hasan. He plays it uppishly past the slip cordon for two.
This is pushed a bit wider of the off stump, Nurul Hasan goes back and across to defend it out.
Length again, around off, Nurul eases it towards cover.
On a good length, outside off. This is played towards cover-point.

EDGED AND FOUR! Nurul Hasan living dangerously here. Around the top of off, Nurul gets another outside edge that goes off the keeper's pads and over the man at first slip. The ball runs away into the third man fence.
Edged but falls well short. This is around off and skidding through, Nurul Hasan looks to driven but gets an outside edge that lands in front of the man at first slip.
Good-length, over middle. Nurul Hasan works it nicely in front of square on the leg side for a couple of runs. Bangladesh trail by only 16 runs now.
Inswinger once again on a good length, It is in line with the stumps and Nurul Hasan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Better length from Jayden Seales attacking the stumps, Nurul Hasan defends it soundly towards cover.
Slightly back of a length outside off. Defended towards point.
Jayden Seales bowls this on a good length outside off. The ball nips in and misses the off stump as Nurul Hasan leaves the ball.
Good-length delivery outside off, Shakib Al Hasan works it to point for a single.

FOUR! Flowing drive from Shakib Al Hasan! Jayden Seales comes around the wicket and angles the ball in from outside off stump. Shakib Al Hasan strides forward to a full delivery and caresses it through covers for a beautiful boundary!
Kyle Mayers just pulls back the length a bit and bowls it outside off. Nurul Hasan goes on the back foot and gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. Maiden!
Nurul Hasan walks down the pitch and converts the length ball into a full ball as he plays it towards cover.
Goes wider of the crease and angles it in a long way into off stump. Nurul keeps it out.
Beaten! On a fuller length and outside off, this one just holds its line. Nurul Hasan plays inside the line of the ball and is beaten past the outside edge.
Full, shaping into off stump. This is nicely driven towards mid off.
On a length and angling into middle and leg. Nurul keeps it out on the leg side.
Good length from Jayden Seales on the off stump, Shakib Al Hasan plays it back to the bowler.
Wide delivery on a good length. Stays a bit low as Shakib Al Hasan offers no shot.
Back-of-a-length delivery this time. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and knocks it to covers.

FOUR! Huge stride forward and leans into this one! Jayden Seales bowls full outside off. Shakib Al Hasan shows good footwork and thumps it through covers. Some ordinary fielding at the boundary gives Shakib four runs.
Jayden Seales bowls the same delivery and Shakib Al Hasan continues to let it go.
Jayden Seales begins with a good-length delivery wide from off stump and angling away, Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone.
Jayden Seales comes back into the attack replacing Kemar Roach.
It's the change-up delivery from Kyle Mayers this time. Goes wider of the crease and angles it in full and into middle. Nurul Hasan pushes it out towards covers.
Length again, around off. Nurul goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Keeping a shade low. Angled in from outside off, Nurul gets behind the line to make the block.
On a good length, around off. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and taps it towards cover-point for one.
Top of the off stump line, kept out on the off side.
This is angled in on a fuller length and into leg stump. Shakib backs away and defends it out.
Around the top of off and jagging back in. Nurul Hasan looks to drive but checks his shot and keeps it out.
Just a bit too straight from Roach at the moment, this is flicked towards mid-wicket.
This is angled into middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.

Lovely shot but it is stopped well. Full and straight, Nurul Hasan drives it straight back past the bowler but Raymon Reifer is quick to get to his left from mid on and make the stop. Nurul wants the single but Shakib sends him back.
Uppish but in the gap. Overpitched, outside off, Shakib Al Hasan drives it uppishly through the vacant cover-point region and rotates the strike.
On a fuller length and angling into off, Shakib solidly blocks it out.
Beaten! Mayers goes a bit fuller and on the fifth stump line, Nurul Hasan looks to have a poke at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, angling into off. Nurul plays it towards the gully region.
Kyle Mayers goes wider of the crease and outside off, Nurul makes yet another leave.
This is pitched up, around off. Nurul Hasan lets it through to the keeper.

This is on a shorter length and outside off. Nurul walks towards the ball and edges it down with soft hands past gully. The fielder from backward point gives chase and keeps it down to a couple of runs.
On a fullish length, around the pads. Shakib tucks it past square leg for one.
Very full and on off, this is firmly driven towards long off for a single.
Two more and Bangladesh now trail by 34 runs. Back of a length, around off. Shakib hops and punches it through cover-point for a brace.
This is pitched up around off, this is driven through covers for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Short and wide, punished! This is short and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan plays the horizontal bat shot and slaps it behind point for a boundary.
Roach switches to around the wicket for the left-hander and keeps it outside off. Shakib mistimes it towards mid off.
A length ball, angling it in from outside off. Nurul Hasan looks to cover drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket. A single is taken.
FOUR! Shot! Too full in length and around off, Shakib skips down the track and crunches his drive past the right side of the mid off fielder for a boundary.
Fuller and around off, Shakib walks forward and drives but finds mid off.
Lands it on a length, around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.

Huge appeal again, for an lbw. The finger stays down. On a length, around off, hitting the seam and going through Shakib's defense. It clips a bit of his pad but it's too high. The replays, later on, show that there was a faint inside edge. No one appealed for a caught behind there, the ball had carried to the keeper. An opportunity missed.
On a length, around off, defended to the off side.

Shout for an lbw, a huge one but the umpire shakes his head. Mayers delivers an inswinger, around off and on a fuller length. Shakib walks forward and across and tries to flick but misses. He is thudded on the pads and West Indies put an unsuccessful appeal. The hosts take the DRS. The impact is outside 3 meters and Shakib remains not out.
Kyle Mayers (8-2-16-2) to bowl from the opposite end.
Unplayable. Angling in on a length around off, Nurul stays back to defend but is beaten by the late away movement. Could have edged it multiple times in this over but Nurul is lucky.
This one is angled in around off, on a fuller length, Nurul looks more assured as he presses forward and defends it to mid on.
Lands it on a length and outside off, staying low, Nurul crouches a bit as he keeps it out to point.
Once again there is some late away movement. Around off, Nurul pushes and misses inside the line.

Confusion over a run. A length ball around off, Nurul pushes it firmly to mid off. Slight fumble there and Hasan looks for a run. Shakib sends him back as the fielder sends a wayward throw towards the keeper.
Beats the edge straight away. Late movement for Kemar Roach, from a length around off, Nurul pokes at it and misses.

We are back for the post-Lunch session! It's now a test of survival for Shakib Al Hasan and his men. It remains to be seen as to for how long they can deny what looks to be inevitable. The umpires and the fielders are back on the field as Shakib Al Hasan and Nurul Hasan take guard. It will be Kemar Roach, the man who made meaningful inroads towards the end of the first session, to get things going with the ball after the break.
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

Kemar Roach and Jayden Seales didn't quite start off in the manner they would have liked to but the introduction of Kyle Mayers into the attack paid dividends as he picked up a couple of wickets. Alzarri Joseph too was a bit on the shorter side and was ineffective but Roach made a strong comeback in his second spell of the day, sending back two more Bangladeshi batters to put his team right on top of proceedings. With the game firmly in West Indies' corner and Bangladesh having it all to do, it remains to be seen as to how Shakib Al Hasan approaches his innings. Will the Windies wrap things up in the post-Lunch session? We'll find out soon. The afternoon session will start at 10.10 pm IST (4.40 pm GMT). Do join us then to find out how things unfold.

Bangladesh came into Day 3 trailing by 112 runs and Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mahmudul Hasan Joy did start off well negotiating the Windies pacers. After that, a couple of wickets fell in quick succession and Litton Das walked in and started playing his shots. This helped Bangladesh to take a big chunk out of the deficit but it also provided opportunities for the hosts to grab some wickets. The visitors then lost two more wickets and are now left struggling with just 4 wickets in hand and trailing by 47 runs. The skipper, Shakib Al Hasan is the only one who can now help his side avoid an innings defeat but he will require ample support from Nurul Hasan from the other end in order to do so.

Session summary - 29 overs, 65 runs and 4 wickets! It has been yet another highly productive session for West Indies in the field. They have managed to pick up as many as four wickets whilst keeping their lead intact which currently stands at 47 runs. With just a couple of more recognized batters left at the crease for Bangladesh, the hosts will look to come back fresh after the Lunch interval and wrap up the innings at the earliest. If they manage to do so, the game could finish in the second session itself.
Flights it up and serves it full around off, Shakib Al Hasan leans forward and defends it safely. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Flatter and a touch shorter, around off, Shakib Al Hasan goes on the back foot and blocks it down.
Fullish and on off, Shakib walks forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller and around off, it's driven through extra cover for a single. Nurul wants the second run but is sent back.
Floated and full, around off, Nurul gets opened up in his stance as he defends it back.
Slightly short and around off, Shakib gets back and deflects it behind backward point for a run.
Brilliant delivery. Roach goes wide of the crease and angles it on a length around off. Nurul Hasan takes a big stride forward to cover the stumps and shoulders arms.
Fuller and on off, it's forced back off the front foot. Roach stops it in his followthrough.
On a length and outside off, Nurul punches it from the back foot to covers.
Lands it full and outside off, Shakib leans forward and drives it through cover-point for a run. The deficit drops under 50 now.
Pitches it up and around off, Shakib pushes it defensively to short cover.
Full and around off, angling in, Shakib gets forward and defends.
Too full in length, around off, Nurul lunges and defends it back to the bowler.
Advances down the track to a full ball around off and knocks it down towards mid on for a run.
Presses forward and drives a full ball past the bowler. Alzarri Joseph cuts it off at mid off and they cross for a run.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Nurul pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Short again, turning in from around off, Shakib moves back and cuts it towards point for one.
Flatter and on off, Shakib goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Close to off, on a length and holding its line, it's a brave leave by Nurul.
Fuller and on off, defended off the front foot.
Edged but safe. Nurul Hasan chases a length ball outside off and edges it behind. It falls in front of the slip cordon.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Nurul Hasan is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another avoidable shot has been played, and this time by the set batter. Back of a length, outside off and shaping away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy rises on the back foot and throws his bat needlessly at this one. The outside edge gets generated and Joshua Da Silva completes the catch diving across to his right. Things unravelling very quickly for Bangladesh here. They still trail by 53 runs and have only four wickets in the bank.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller in length, around off and angling in, Joy flicks it through mid-wicket and scampers back for the second run. The deficit is now 53 runs.
Floated delivery, full and around off, Shakib jumps down the track and drives it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off, Shakib stays back to defend and keeps it out off the outer half of his blade.
Around off, spinning in, the batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Loopy and around off, turning in, Shakib tries to flick but only manages to push it back, a shade uppishly. Doesn't carry to the bowler.
Fuller and around off, turning away a shade, Joy lunges to defend but it takes the outer edge and rolls to the left of point. They cross.
Slower through the air, full and around middle, Joy defends it back.
Spears it in full, around middle and leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy clips it to deep square leg for one.
Outside off, on a length and holding its line, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Some inward movement again, Joy once again looks to defend close to his body but inside-edges it onto his pads.
On a length and close to off, Joy tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and around off, driven back to the bowler.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Beaten! This one doesn't spin back in much, Shakib plays for the turn off the front foot as it whistles past the outside edge.
Full outside off,  turning back in, Shakib Al Hasan tries to hammer this but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Flatter and shorter around off, punched in front of square on the off side for a run.
Flighted and around off, defended off the front foot. Joshua Da Silva quips from behind the stumps - 'Nobody wants to stick around, a lot of pressure here boys, not too many shots being played here!'
A touch shorter and flatter around off, Shakib moves back and nudges it in front of square leg for a run.
Loopy and full, around off, Shakib presses forward and defends.

Beauty! Roach goes wide of the crease and slants in a shortish ball around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hangs on the back foot like a dead duck as he has a tame push inside the line. The ball though moves away late to beat the outside edge.
Lands it on a length and around off, Joy taps it down from the back foot to cover-point.
Angling in, fuller and around off, Joy strokes it down the ground. Finds mid on again.
Slightly behind a good length, around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays solid in his defense from the back foot.
Pitches it up and outside off, inviting the drive, Mahmudul Hasan Joy obliges but finds mid off.
Fuller and in the zone around middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it down to mid on.

Bye! Nicely floated around off and the ball turns away square. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks for the expansive drive but is beaten and the keeper misses the ball as well. The batters scamper through for a bye.
Full and angled into middle-leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it towards mid-wicket.
Full and on off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted on off stump. Defended solidly.
Quicker delivery on a good length, angling down leg side. Missed by Shakib Al Hasan and the keeper and they get an extra run as bye.
Flighted on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy cuts it to deep point for a single.

Oooh, a bit of aggression straightaway from the skipper. Kemar Roach goes a bit wider of the off stump and Shakib just looks to clobber it away. Shakib is beaten comprehensively though. Hard to believe this approach.
This is angled into off from around the wicket. Shakib Al Hasan solidly keeps it out.
Shakib Al Hasan is in next. The best batter of the team is batting at number 7.

OUT! CAUGHT! A loose shot from Litton Das and Kemar Roach strikes in his first over of a new spell. This is served on a good length outside off and the ball zips off the surface. Das looks to drive away from the body but his feet go nowhere. The ball takes the outside edge and Kyle Mayers takes a sharp catch around his chest at first slip. Just when Bangladesh looked to be on a roll, a wicket goes down. You cannot waft at a wide delivery in the name of positive batting. This is poor from Bangladesh and Litton.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Mayers b Kemar Roach

Commentary.Commentary: Length this time, angling onto the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it behind square on the leg side for one and the 100 is up for Bangladesh They trail by 62 runs now.
Full and straight, this is flicked past mid-wicket for a run.
Roach misses his mark first up and serves a high full toss on off. Litton Das is taken aback and ends up punching it towards mid on.
Kemar Roach (11-6-23-0) is back on.
Bowls this one quicker on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets forward and defends. Gudakesh Motie starts of with a maiden!
Flighted close to the stumps. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends solidly.
Straighter but continues bowling full. It's defended back to the bowler.
Full once again, on leg. Worked towards mid-wicket.
Full and wide spinning away from the off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go.
Flighted full on middle, played back to the bowler.
Gudakesh Motie is now introduced into the attack.
FOUR! The runs are coming thick and fast now for Bangladesh. Back of a length, outside off, this is played on the up and well-manoeuvred past point for a lovely boundary.
On a hard length, around off. Litton Das hangs back and caresses it towards cover-point.
Joseph keeps it a bit short and around off. Das keeps it out off the back foot.
Short of a good length, this is played off the back foot through covers for a single.
Around the top of off, pushed out towards cover.
Length ball, around off. This is pushed towards the cover region for a run.
Kyle Mayers decides to bowl full this time on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy strokes it to mid off.

FOUR! Wide and Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes the most of it! Kyle Mayers bowls on a good length but errs in line. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets on his back foot and opens the face of his bat to find the third man boundary!
Outside off, on a good length. Mahmudul Hasan Joy punches it past covers for a couple of runs.
Slower delivery, full and outside off, Keeps low as Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go.
Wide from off stump and slightly short. Mahmudul Hasan Joy slashes it to point.
Kyle Mayers bowls full and angles it into the stumps. Litton Das works it through square leg for a single.
On a good length, around off. This is defended out by Joy.
Around the top of off, Das looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Two in a row! Alzarri Joseph overcompensates with a half-volley outside off, Das creams this one through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Pulled away! This is banged in short and over middle. Litton Das lays into the shot and pulls it with disdain into the mid-wicket fence.
Back of a length, around off. This is punched towards cover.

Huge appeal for LBW...turned down! Alzarri Joseph serves this one on a length and angles it in from around off. Litton Das shoulders arms at it and gets hit on the back leg. Kraigg Brathwaite goes for the review at the last second. There was no shot offered by Litton Das so the third umpire will go directly to Ball Tracking. It shows that indeed the ball was going over the middle stump and it will stay NOT OUT.
Slightly full outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy knocks it to short cover.
Full and angling down leg, Litton Das flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
