Too full in length and outside off, Das reaches out and digs it out to the off side.

Drinks break. A couple of wickets in the second half of the first hour and all the good work done till then by Bangladesh has gone down the drain. Kyle Mayers has done his magic again with his accurate and skilful bowling. Litton Das walks in next and the tourists need a big effort from him.

OUT! GIVEN LBW! Kyle Mayers' clever variations are doing the job for West Indies. His inswinger lands on a length around off, Mominul Haque tries to flick but his bat gets stuck a bit behind the front pad and he gets pinged in front. The appeal is made, and the umpire thinks for a while before lifting his finger. Mominul Haque has a word with his partner and takes the DRS but the Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the leg stump. Umpire's call and Bangladesh lose their fourth wicket. The deficit for them is 87 runs.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kyle Mayers

Commentary.Commentary: Good-length delivery angled into the pads. Mominul Haque defends it towards mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! In the channel outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy taps it down to backward point and calls his partner through for a quick run. Raymon Reifer scores a direct hit at the striker's end and they all appeal. The decision is referred but Mominul Haque is safely in.
Direct hit at the striker's end, is Mominul Haque short of the crease? Nopes, safely in.
Alzarri Joseph goes straighter on a good length. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly short and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy does not play a shot.
Full and angling into middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy strokes it with a straight bat back past the bowler. The mid-on fielder gives chase and restricts it to a brace.
Short once again and wide from off stump, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks for good measure.
Pulls his length back, and bowls outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it towards point.
Alzarri Joseph starts off with a good-length delivery on off, and Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to mid on.

FOUR! Streaky! Finally, Kyle Mayers gets one to just come in with the angle and it almost produces the wicket. Length ball, around off and nipping back in. Mominul Haque tries to push it out on the off side but gets an inside edge past the leg stump and the ball runs away into the fine leg fence.
Mayers pulls back the length a bit and bowls it on off. Mominul Haque hops and keeps it down on the deck.
This is fuller and in that channel around off, yet another leave from Haque.
On a length and a bit closer to the off stump, Haque shoulders arms to it.
And again. This is leaving the left-hander but is just a bit too wide at the moment from Kyle Mayers to make the batter play at it.
Full and outside off, shaping away from the left-hander. No shot is offered by Mominul Haque.
Alzarri Joseph goes wide from off stump on a good length, and Mahmudul Hasan Joy is happy to let it go.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets on his toes and defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery outside off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy raises his arms and lets it go.
Adjusts his length and pulls it back, angling into the stumps. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends solidly.
Full once again on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy plays it once again towards short mid on.
Full delivery angling into the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy knocks it to mid on.
Well stopped! This is short and wide, Mominul Haque hangs back and slaps it towards backward point where Gudakesh Motie makes a really good diving stop.
This is on off stump, Haque blocks it out.

Leg bye! Half an appeal but sliding well down leg. Mayers goes full this time and tries to attack the pads. Mayers bowls it at the toes as Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to flick it away. Joy misses the flick and the ball goes off his pads towards backward square leg. A leg bye is taken and a no ball is called for overstepping.
Length again, around the top of off. This is defended towards cover.
Lovely shape! Kyle Mayers angles this one in from a bit wider of the crease and makes the ball shape away. Joy tries to play at it but is comprehensively beaten.
Length ball, angling in from around off and skidding through. Joy defends it firmly towards mid on.
This is pitched up on the fourth stump line, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms at it.
Uses the angle of the bowler and turns it behind square leg for a run.
Needless from Joy, this attempt can only bring sorrow to his team. Short in length and outside off, extra pace and bounce, Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays back and tries to slam it over point but misses.
Alzarri Joseph is getting some extra pace and zip off this surface. Delivers it on a length and outside off, Joy allows it through and this one carries nicely to the keeper.
This one is served on top of off, short in length again, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is solid in his defense from the back foot.
Back of a length, outside off and shaping in a bit, Mahmudul Hasan Joy allows it through.
Begins his spell with a shortish delivery around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on the back foot as he defends it down.
Alzarri Joseph (6-2-14-2) comes into the attack for the first time today.
Kyle Mayers angles this one in on a fuller length and at the stumps, Mominul Haque pushes it out towards mid on.
Full and around off, defended solidly by Mominul.
Mominul Haque walks in at number 5.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! So often Kyle Mayers does this. He knows his angles and works the magic with his dibbly-dobblies. Kyle Mayers serves three deliveries in the zone outside off but this time he gets close to off and forces the batter to play the line. Najmul Hossain Shanto doesn't do a lot wrong there but the away movement extracts the outside edge from his defensive bat and John Campbell has a simple catch to take at first slip. There was some extra bounce as well. West Indies have their first breakthrough this morning. They still have a lead of 98 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c John Campbell b Kyle Mayers

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length and outside off, once again Shanto lets it be.
Another delivery outside off, Shanto offers no shot.
Outside off, left alone.
Fraction short and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on his toes and defends it back.
A bouncer again, ducked under.
Not exactly full, it's on a good length and around off, Joy stays back and offers a dead bat in defense.
Bouncer to mix things up. Jayden Seales is forcing the batter on the back foot. Joy ducks. Now watch out for the full tempter.
Shortish and on off, allowing the batter time to go on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Around off, on a length, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it from the back foot.
Fuller and on off, moving in the air, Shanto defends it towards short cover.
Edgy! Mayers puts it on a length and close to off, nipping away a hint, Joy pushes inside the line and edges it past gully. He gets a single.
Back of a length, a little too wide outside off, Joy allows it through.
A gentle inswinger, outside off, an easy leave for Mahmudul.
Fuller and around off, shaping into the batter, Joy defends it close to his body.
Kyle Mayers starts by landing a length ball outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes a watchful leave.
Slightly short again, around middle, Joy works it behind square leg and keeps strike.
Digs it in short, around leg, Shanto goes on his toes and works it with gentle hands behind square leg. One is the call and they get it with ease.
On a length around off, Shanto hangs on the back foot and defends it down.

FOUR! Spanked! On the up but he nailed it. Width there outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto latches onto it and smashes it through the line. It's aerial but through the gap between mid off and extra cover.
Back of a length, on top of off, Najmul Hossain Shanto goes on his toes and strokes it to covers.
Angling away from the batter, on a length, Najmul Hossain Shanto lets it be.
A touch short and outside off, Joy goes on the back foot and punches it to point.
Beaten! Kemar Roach gets close to off, angling in on a length and then it nips away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is beaten as he tries to defend the line.
Fuller and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks quite assured in leaving this one. His stance shows that he knows where his off stump is.
On a length and outside off, it's left alone.
In the zone outside off, on a length and shaping away a bit, Joy pushes inside the line and misses.
Full and around off, Mahmudul is on the front foot and defends it down safely. Both the Bangla batters are looking solid in defense.
Too full and around off, Joy tries to drive straight but it takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket. They cross.
Fuller and around off, defended solidly off the front foot.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it safely towards mid on.
Good leave. This one is on a length and close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy takes his front leg forward to cover his stumps and then makes a leave.
Wrong line. Too full and wide down the leg side, the batter attempts to flick but misses.
Fuller in length and around off, it's served from wide of the crease, Joy tries to flick but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads.
A touch short and on off, Shanto defends it with the angle of the bowler to the leg side. Maiden, first of this morning.
Darts in a length ball on off, Shanto is solidly behind the line of the delivery in defense.
On a length and close to off, Shanto guards his stumps and makes a leave. There is some late away movement as it leaves the batter.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Shanto drives it down the ground, from the inner half to mid on.
Back of a length, just outside off and nipping away, Najmul Hossain Shanto stays on the back foot and keeps his bat close to his body. Leaves it.
Spears it in, very full and on off, Shanto drives it back to the bowler. Roach jumps to collect the ball but ends up deflecting it to mid off.
A gentle delivery. A bit short and outside off, holding its line, Mahmudul has nothing to do with it.
Seales serves it full and on off, it's angling in and there isn't much movement present. Mahmudul Hasan Joy covers the line and blocks.
Hurls a length ball in the channel outside off, shaping away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
A bit too straight this time, full and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans across and flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Angling in around off, fuller in length, Joy defends it back with a straight bat.
Fuller and around off, defended watchfully by Mahmudul Hasan Joy.
Jayden Seales who was a bit off his radar late on Day 2 will bowl from the opposite end.
Back of a length, on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and on off, blocked solidly.
A bit of indecision shown by the batter. Outside off, Shanto takes a late call of leaving it. He tries to withdraw the bat but it takes the bottom edge and rolls behind to the slip cordon.

FOUR! Confident shot. Fuller in length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets on the front foot and smacks it through wide mid off for a boundary. Roach won't mind that shot as well, as he got the batter to drive there.
Play and a miss on the second ball. Roach lands it close to off and takes it away with the seam movement. Shanto feels for it and misses it. The ball dies in front of Joshua Da Silva.
Right on the button. Kemar Roach begins from 'round the wicket angle and slants a length ball on off, Shanto defends it to the off side.

We are moments away from the start of the play on Day 3! The weather is a bit cloudy and that might offer the pacers a bit of help early on but as we type, the sun is just starting to peek through the clouds. The umpires are out in the middle and so are the West Indies players. Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mahmudul Hasan Joy are all set to resume their stay at the crease. Kemar Roach will start proceedings with the ball and is raring to go.

PITCH REPORT - Samuel Badree and Sir Curtly Ambrose are pitch side. Badree says that it continues to be a challenging surface for the batters. Sir Curtly says that indeed it will be a challenging day and the grass around the wicket is providing variable bounce and the pacers can use that. Badree adds that spinners might come into play today and Gudakesh Motie might be used more.

What do Bangladesh need on Day 3? As said earlier, they need to bat and bat and bat for as long as possible. To wipe off the deficit will be on top of their agenda and they cannot afford to lose many wickets while doing so. With Mushfiqur Rahim missing, someone like Mominul Haque and Shakib Al Hasan will have to take control of the batting department and provide solidity. It is going to be a litmus test for them this morning, and surviving the first session will be the key. Can they do it with minimum casualty? We will find out soon.

West Indies have done most things right in this Test match, right from winning the toss. Their bowlers have utilized the conditions way better than the touring team and playing in their own backyard has certainly served as an advantage. The hosts would be aiming to repeat their bowling show of the first day and make early inroads this morning. Can Roach and company dominate proceedings yet again?

Welcome back, folks. The third day of this Test match is upon us and clearly, it's West Indies who hold all the aces and can call the shots. The great work done by their bowlers on the first day has had a lasting impact and Bangladesh have not recovered since then. The tourists did show some spark with the ball last evening but that's too little to change the landscape of this game. A massive batting effort is the need of the hour and let's see if the Bangla Tigers have it in them to find their feet in this match. Stay tuned for more...
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 ...

Right then, two days have flown by in this Test match and there are still three days left but at the moment it doesn't look like the game will stretch that long. Day 3 is known as the moving day and if West Indies do get early wickets then the day could move along at a rapid pace and even prove to be the last day of the game. It has been an exciting contest between bat and ball so far and the same should continue on Day 3. Action will begin at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT) but our build-up will begin much sooner. Do join us then. Cheers!

Mehidy Hasan is down for a quick chat. He says that he was disappointed with his first couple of spells as he didn't bowl in the correct areas. Shares that he then mentally prepared himself and got some help from the spinners not playing this game and was able to pick up wickets. Mentions that his plan was to pile on the dot balls which would put pressure on the batters. Further says that at first, he tried too hard to get wickets but changed his game plan later on. Adds that it was an opportunity for him after being sent at one down but unfortunately it didn't come off and he will try harder next time. Reckons that they have quality batters and the key is to bat the whole of Day 3.

Bangladesh have their work cut out with the bat and even after some really excellent bowling, it is the poor showing with the bat in the first innings that is costing them dearly here. After toiling hard, their bowlers were able to make use of the second new ball and Mehidy Hasan ended up with four wickets. In their second innings, Bangladesh trailed by 162 runs but it was a pretty breezy start from their openers, especially Tamim Iqbal who did get out after getting a start. Mehidy Hasan came in ahead of other top-order batters but the move didn't work. Since then, Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Najmul Hossain Shanto have done a decent job of standing their ground but it will require a lot more than just that if they are to have any chance of turning the match in their favour.

West Indies came into Day 2 with 8 wickets in hand and seemed to be going along nicely but as soon as the second new ball was taken, their middle order fell prey to some probing bowling by the opposition. A lead that looked to be going beyond 200 runs ended up being 162 runs which was still sizeable. On the bowling front, Alzarri Joseph has delivered for them after an uncharacteristic start from Kemar Roach and Jayden Seales in the second innings. They will now look to get some rest and come back to pick up early wickets on Day 3.

Another day of Test cricket is done and just like Day 1, West Indies seem to be in command of the match. 12 wickets fell on Day 1 and as many as 10 wickets have fallen on Day 2 which shows that the pitch still has a bit in it for the bowlers. Bangladesh currently trail by 112 runs and with 8 wickets in hand, it will take a big effort from their batters on Day 3 to first cut down the deficit entirely and then give their bowlers something to bowl at. A difficult task but we'll see how things play out on Saturday.
Shorter one again around middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath it. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Shorter and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go towards the keeper.
Touch fuller in length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it through covers for a brace. That brings up the 50 for Bangladesh. They now trail by 112 runs.
This was similar to the last delivery, Mahmudul Hasan Joy again defends it back towards the bowler.
This is on a good length and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy eases it back towards Alzarri Joseph.
Goes shorter and on leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath it.
FOUR! No trouble with the leg there! Full once again and straying outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets a confident stride forward and caresses it wide of mid off for a wonderful boundary!
Full and angling in from outside off stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto strides his front foot forward and defends firmly.

Najmul Hossain Shanto seems to be in a bit of discomfort out there. As Shanto defended the ball a couple of deliveries ago, he started hobbling. He already has a strapping on the left leg from an earlier injury which now seems to be aggravated. The physio is out to have a look. Hope he is fine.
Good-length delivery pitching outside off and then moving away from the left-handed batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto tries to feel for it and gets beaten.
Full once again and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto knocks it to covers.
Goes fuller this time outside off, keeps low and Najmul Hossain Shanto manages to bring his bat down in time to smother it.
Effort ball from Kemar Roach but does not make the batter play at it. Full and outside off, left alone with ease.
On a length angling it into the batter, Mahmudul Hasan Joy guides it to cover and straight towards the fielder.
Bowls it outside off and slightly shorter in length, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it towards the mid on region.

FOUR! This is an excellent and perfectly timed shot from Mahmudul Hasan Joy. Fuller and down the middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays firm and drives it straight down the ground. Alzarri Joseph just gets his hand on it but the ball races towards long off for a boundary.
Goes outside off this time, Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go towards the keeper.
Bowls it on a good length with some extra bounce, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it solidly.
Roach goes full and straight now, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it out solidly.
Pitched up, around off, left alone.
Early call for two and they will get it with ease, good running. This is angled into the pads, Najmul Hossain Shanto turns it past square leg this time and races back for the second.
Streaky but in the gap. Fuller, on a driving length and angling in from outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it through the cover region and picks up a couple of runs.
On a length, closer to the off stump. Well watched and well left by Najmul Hossain Shanto.
Full and wide, from around the stumps, left alone by Najmul Hossain Shanto.
Kemar Roach is back into the attack.
Another maiden from Alzarri Joseph. Fuller in length and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy guides it straight towards the fielder at short cover.
Outside off this time and on a length, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Goes shorter this time and down the leg side, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath it.
Bowls it on a length and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy punches it towards short cover.
Touch fuller and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it on a good length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it back towards the bowler.
Kyle Mayers adjusts his line and gets it just outside off, angling into the batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto judges the line well and leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on middle. Knocked towards mid on by Najmul Hossain Shanto.
Kyle Mayers tries bowling this one fuller outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto connects it well towards the cover region.
Full and wide from the stumps. Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it to short cover.
Full on off stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto knocks it to mid on.
Continues bowling around the wicket to the left-hander. Outside off stump and full. Left alone by Najmul Hossain Shanto
A maiden from Alzarri Joseph. Back of a length angling it into the batter, Mahmudul Hasan Joy punches it towards the cover fielder.
This is outside off again, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Length ball but this is wide outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
Change of length again. Goes fuller and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards the mid on fielder.
Back of a length, outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms at it.
Touch fuller delivery and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Full and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it firmly to mid off.
Wide of the off stump, going away from the batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto watches as it passes him and goes through to the keeper.
Kyle Mayers comes around the wicket and bowls on a good-length, this time on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto defends this back down the pitch.
Good-length delivery angled into leg stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it to square leg for a single.
Another one beats the bat. Kyle Mayers pulls this slightly back and continues bowling with a wobble seam. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hangs his bat out and does not connect.
Kyle Mayers starts off with a beauty! Wobble seam outside off stump. Moves away from a good length and beats Mahmudul Hasan Joy with ease.
Kyle Mayers is now brought into the attack.
Outside off this time, Najmul Hossain Shanto guides it towards the off side.
Fuller in length and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto leans forward and defends it towards the point fielder.
Najmul Hossain Shanto is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Alzarri Joseph with his second wicket in as many overs and the idea of sending Mehidy Hasan up the order hasn't worked for Bangladesh. This is bowled on a good length and close to the off stump. Joseph does get a bit of an extra bounce due to his height. Mehidy Hasan looks to get on top of the bounce and punch it off the back foot but only manages to get an outside edge. Kyle Mayers at first slip takes a safe catch around his chest and Bangladesh are two down now.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Mayers b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Bowls it outside off this time, Mehidy Hasan puts his bat at it. The ball rolls towards the fielder at slips.
Serves a fuller one down the leg side, Mehidy Hasan flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Back of a length, down the middle, Mehidy Hasan defends it solidly.
Fuller once again on middle and off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy goes through with the shot but gets a thick edge to point.
Good-length delivery on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends on the front foot with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy knocks it towards mid off.
Swings away from the batter, bowled on a wide line slightly full. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Inswinger, on a good length, close to the off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy plays at it and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Kemar Roach bowls this slightly full outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets this go through to the keeper.
Back of a length, around off. This is dabbed down towards backward point.
Around the top of off, Mehidy Hasan backs away a bit and keeps it out towards cover.

DRINKS! A strong start from Bangladesh but it has now come to a halt as Tamim Iqbal is sent back. The visitors will hope to not repeat their mistakes from the first innings and keep wickets in hand heading into Day 3. West Indies will like to build on this breakthrough and pick up a couple of more wickets before the close of play. With that being said, Mehidy Hasan walks in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Joshua Da Silva with an exceptional catch behind the stumps and Tamim Iqbal has to depart. Strong comeback by Alzarri Joseph and he provides the first breakthrough for West Indies. This is bowled on a perfect length, in that channel close to the off stump. Once again, Tamim Iqbal tries to have a nibble at it and the hint of away movement catches the outside edge of Iqbal's willow. The ball flies through to towards first slip but Joshua Da Silva springs to his left and takes a one-handed stunner. Bangladesh trail by 129 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary.Commentary: Keeps low! This is banged in short and around off, Tamim Iqbal tries to seat under it but the ball keeps low and just goes over his head.
FOUR! Not an ideal start by Alzarri Joseph and Tamim Iqbal punishes him. Another half-volley, this time on the pads and this is flicked away into the mid-wicket fence.
Starts off with a loosener does Alzarri Joseph. This is a half-volley outside off, Tamim Iqbal drives it through the cover region for a couple of runs.
First change in the bowling as Alzarri Joseph replaces Jayden Seales.

A bit of a mix-up but no harm is done. This is full again from Kemar Roach and around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy strokes it to the right of the man at mid off. Joy looks for the single but Tamim Iqbal isn't even looking at him. Joy just about manages to scamper back in time.
Full again, on off. Joy defends it firmly towards silly mid on.
Full and around off, Joy leans forward to block it out.
Loose shot this time around from Joy. On a shorter length, outside off and shaping away. Joy looks to play away from the body but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Solid from Joy! On a fuller length, around off and nipping back in sharply. Joy keeps it out on the off side.
Goes fuller this time and angles it into middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pushes it out towards mid on.
Another full toss as Jayden Seales loses his radar a bit. This time Tamim punches it back towards the bowler. A solid start so far from the Bangladeshi openers.
FOUR! A juicy full toss now as Jayden Seales overcompensates for the short ball. Tamim Iqbal flicks it through the vacant mid-wicket region to make it back-to-back boundaries.
FOUR! Up and over, deliberately played! Short and wide, Tamim Iqbal hops and upper-cuts it over the backward point region to find the fence.
Well bowled! On a length, slanted across the off stump. Tamim Iqbal has a nibble at it as he looks to play away from the body but is beaten past the outside edge.
Fullish delivery, in the channel around off and angling away. Tamim Iqbal makes a stylish leave.
Overpitched this time from Jayden Seales, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pushes it down the ground past the man at mid on and comes back for the third run.
Pitches it up, outside off, Tamim Iqbal tries to drive through the line but mistimes it to mid off.
Around off, on a length and going straight on, Tamim pushes inside the line and misses.
Angles in a length ball around off, Tamim covers the line and blocks it safely.
Back of a length, around off, hitting the deck hard, Tamim is on the back foot in defense.
Fuller in length and outside off, it's driven confidently off the front foot but straight to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Surprises the batter with his inswinger. Around off, on a length, Mahmudul defends it back from the crease.
Back of a length, outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy crouches and evades it.
Seales is showing good discipline. Bowling his outswingers in a nice grouping, just outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Fullish and around off, Joy pushes it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
On a length and outside off, nipping away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy allows it through to the keeper. He is standing ahead of the crease to negate the movement.
A bumper close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Tamim keeps his bat close to his body and lets it be.
Fuller and outside off, driven through the line but not in the gap.

EDGED BUT SAFE! A defensive prod from Tamim this time, he tries to block a length ball which is angled into him. The ball though moves away to take the outside edge. Doesn't carry to John Campbell at second slip.
Better this time from the experienced campaigner. An outswinger outside off, this time Tamim respects the bowler and his delivery. Leaves it alone.
Play and a miss! Roach puts it on a fuller length outside off, Tamim aims for a booming drive but is beaten by the away movement.
Confusion but no harm is done. Fuller and around middle, Tamim nudges it to mid-wicket and comes out searching for a run. His partner sends him back in time.
Close to off, on a length, it's defended to covers.
Seales gets greedy. Tries to bowl an outswinger from the middle stump line. But this one pitches and goes down with the angle as the batter watches it.
Similar to the last delivery but the line goes wide outside off, an easy leave for Joy.
Angles it in, on a length and close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Around middle, on a length, Tamim works it away from the mid-wicket fielder and takes a single.
Drifting down the leg side, Tamim tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to the keeper. Tamim got strangled down the leg side in the first innings and needs to be careful.
FOUR! Delightful. Fuller in length and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans forward and plays a crunchy square drive for a boundary.

Roach goes wide of the crease and lands it on a length outside off, Joy is in two minds, eventually tries to leave but is late in withdrawing his bat. It takes the bottom edge and rolls away towards the slip cordon.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it on the leg side.
Beautifully bowled. Roach hurls across a length ball, around off and getting it to straighten a hint, Mahmudul Hasan Joy feels for it inside the line and misses.
Around off, on a length and angling in, Tamim shows the full face of his bat and punches it down to mid on. The fielder cuts it off and they take a run.
Tamim is looking to play his shots. Fuller in length, around middle, Iqbal flicks it through mid-wicket for two.
In the region outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes a watchful leave.
Mahmudul Hasan Joy is away in this Test match. Back of a length, around off, Joy pushes inside the line and edges it wide of gully. Takes two.
Perfect line and length to beat the bat. Jayden Seales gets close to off, and delivers an outswinger. Joy has no joy in dealing with it. Tries to play the line but is beaten by the movement.
On a good length around off, defended down from the back foot.
Another outswinger outside off, another easy leave. Seales needs to get closer to the stumps.
A gentle outswinger to begin his spell. It's outside off and easily left by Mahmudul Hasan Joy.
Jayden Seales to steam in from the other end.
A dot to end the first over. Fuller this time and closer to the off stump.Tamim Iqbal plays inside the line of the ball as the ball zips past the outside edge.

Loose shot from Tamim Iqbal and he is fortunate to not chop it back onto the stumps. Kemar Roach angles this one from outside off, Iqbal has a tentative push at it and gets a bottom edge that doesn't go on to hit the off pole.
A tad shorter in length, around off. Tamim Iqbal pushes it out towards cover.
On a good length, slightly closer to the off stump. This time around Tamim Iqbal punches it off the back foot but can't pierce the gap on the off side.

FOUR! Tamim Iqbal is underway with a boundary! Back of a length and outside off, Iqbal waits on the back foot and slaps it through cover-point. Kraigg Brathwaite gives chase and seems to have just pulled it back in time. The replay though shows that Kraigg Brathwaite was in contact with the ropes as he pulled the ball back in and it will be a boundary.
Starts off with a short ball around off. There's good bounce on offer and Tamim Iqbal does well to hop and keeps it down on the off side.

That's all we have from this Test match. West Indies have taken the lead and also crucial points for the ICC World Test Championship. The second Test starts on Friday, 24th June 2022 at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT). Do join us in advance for the coverage. Until then, it's goodbye and cheers!

Kraigg Brathwaite, the victorious skipper of West Indies, says that they bowled really well and as a group, they batted decently. Feels it could have been better with the bat in the first innings. Adds that the coaching staff has done a great job and Roach is leading the bowling attack really well. Mentions that Roach's spell set the tone and he is a champion player for them. Tells that Roach has a heart of a champion and brings a lot of values. States that they are looking forward to the challenge in St Lucia and he has a word of praise for the Bangla bowlers as well. He is pleased with the knock of John Campbell and is glad that he remained unbeaten. Shares that they trust in the abilities of Raymon Reifer at number 3 and want to invest in him.

Shakib Al Hasan, the Bangladesh skipper, says that losing the toss played a significant part but they cannot complain. Adds that the pitch was tough but they could have applied themselves better. Mentions that one session killed the game for them. He is happy with the way his bowlers performed. States that this kind of batting is not acceptable and they have been doing that regularly now. Feels that the batters need to find a way to survive and then the bowlers will win you the game. Talks about his stand with Nurul Hasan and says that there is a lot to learn for other batters from Nurul's knock. On his personal form, Shakib replies that he was positive in his approach and kept his game simple.

Kemar Roach is the Player of the Match! The speedster says that his family is very proud of him and it's a good feeling to help the fans get happy. Mentions that it's a great feeling to equal Michael Holding's record and wants to keep working and get to 300 Test wickets. He thanks all his coaches who have taught him the fundamentals of bowling and is happy to have those guys in his career. States that they were just looking to be patient during the century stand between Shakib and Nurul. Feels that they did that really well and praises the supporting bowlers. He ranks this performance of his in his top five at this stadium.
Presentation coming up...

All is not gloomy for Bangladesh. As a visiting team, it's always tough to acclimatize to the conditions, especially for the batters. Spending time at the crease even though the runs are not coming is crucial. It is something they can learn from the old-school batting of Kraigg Brathwaite. The real essence of batting in a Test match lies in patience. Sometimes you've to grind hard, and the best example of that was the century stand between Shakib Al Hasan and Nurul Hasan. They invested their time at the crease, and once the pitch eased out and the ball got softer, they booked profit. On the bowling front, all the three pacers were brilliant. They got the skills and if the batters complement them, Bangladesh can script a comeback at St Lucia.

The West Indian bowling was exceptional and it was spearheaded by Kemar Roach. His participation was in doubt before this Test match, but he passed the fitness test and left a huge impact. Jayden Seales and Alzarri Joseph were also excellent in their supporting roles while Kyle Mayers was the joker in the pack. With his dibbly-dobblies, Mayers impressed, and his skilful bowling helped the hosts in getting vital breakthroughs.

This Test match was dominated by the bowlers. 12 wickets fell on Day 1, 10 on Day 2, and 11 on the third day. In between, there were knocks from Kraigg Braithwaite, Jermaine Blackwood and Nkrumah Bonner in the first innings to hand a 162-run lead to the home team. Bangladesh's batting surrendered in both innings. Only Shakib Al Hasan managed twin fifties, and his century stand with Nurul Hasan on Day 3 was the silver lining for the touring team. They will have to show better application and temperament, especially with the bat, in the next Test to compete in these conditions.

All over in a flash! Nothing surprising or miraculous happened this morning, as West Indies got the remaining runs with ease in seven overs. John Campbell remained unbeaten on 58 and his 79-run stand with Jermaine Blackwood, in a tricky situation, will do his confidence a world of good. Smiles in the West Indian camp and the players are shaking hands on the ground.
SIX! Campbell finishes it off in style! Tossed up around off, fuller in length, John Campbell latches onto it and smacks it all the way over long off for a biggie. West Indies win by 7 wickets!
Short and outside off, Campbell goes hard at it and mistimes his square-cut to covers.
Fuller and around off, defended off the front foot.
Short in length and outside off, John cracks it off his back foot but finds the cover fielder.
FOUR! Full and flighted, around middle, Campbell gets down on one knee and sweeps it to fine leg for a boundary. FIFTY FOR CAMPBELL! Two needed more.
Drifting down the leg side, John moves back and helps it to square leg.
Najmul Hossain Shanto to bowl.
Extra loop on this delivery. It lands and breaks back in, Jermaine Blackwood lunges to defend and keeps it out off the inner half to square leg.
Mehidy pulls his length back and lands it around off, Jermaine Blackwood goes on the back foot and offers a dead bat.
Loopy and full, around off, Jermaine is on the front foot in defense.
Quicker and around off, again it's blocked from the back foot.
Flatter and a touch shorter, around off, it's defended from the back foot.
Starts by delivering it very full, around off and drifting in, Blackwood pushes it down to mid on.
Mehidy Hasan comes into the attack.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Campbell moves to 48 with this boundary. Fuller in length and outside off, John presses forward and strokes it elegantly through covers.
In the channel outside off, on a length and going almost straight on with extra bounce, Campbell attempts the punch but away from the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Extra bounce this time, on a length and outside off, Campbell plays at it with an angled bat and guides it with soft hands. Deliberately keeps it down and places it wide of the slip cordon. The ball races away to the third man fence. 10 more to win.
Serves it on a length again, outside off and shaping back in, John covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, a hint of inward shape there, Campbell plays inside the line and lets it through to the keeper.
On a length and outside off, angling in, Campbell presses forward and gently pushes it to the off side.
Fraction short, around off and shaping back in, Blackwood stays back and glances it behind square leg for a couple.
Back of a length, wide outside off, Campbell stays back and cuts it through backward point for a single.
Back of a length, on off, John is on the back foot in defense.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Jermaine Blackwood takes a positive stride forward and drives it through covers for three runs.
This time there is some extra bounce as it lands on a good length and holds its line outside off. Jermaine Blackwood goes fishing for it and gets beaten.
Fuller and outside off, pushed back off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and wide, cut from the back foot but straight to the point fielder.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Helps a full ball off his pads to backward square leg for a run.
Lands it on a length, outside off, it's defended back.
A hint of inward movement there, from a length around off, Campbell closes the face of his bat and nudges it through backward square leg. Calls for two and gets two. 10 from the over!
Slants it in, on a good length around off, Campbell goes on the back foot and defends it down on the pitch.
FOUR! Bang! The 50-run stand comes up. Short in length and wide outside off, John Campbell stands tall inside the crease and slaps it through point for another boundary. 23 more needed.
FOUR! First of the boundary. Angling down the leg side, on a length, Campbell clips it off his pads and it scoots away to the fine leg fence. 27 needed more.
Play and a miss! Short in length and outside off, Campbell tries to cut but it bounces over his blade.
Ebadot runs in from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball on off, Campbell defends it from the front foot.
Ebadot Hossain is to operate from the other end.
Lands it full and on off, John defends it off the front foot to point. They cross for a run.
A bit of movement, from a length around off, Jermaine taps it down to point and takes a run.
Around off, a bit full in length, Blackwood is forward as he defends.
On a length and outside off, easy leave for the batter again.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller in length, around leg, it's clipped behind square leg for a couple.
Time to get underway! The players are on the field. Khaled Ahmed to begin proceedings. Can he make early inroads again and scare the home team? Let's find out...
Pitch report - The surface has proved to be challenging for batting, with a bit of grass and some bare areas. We have seen some variable bounce as well.

Roddy Estwick, the assistant coach of West Indies, comes up for a chat. He says that their bowling lost the plot a bit on Day 3 and he would rate it 6.5 out of 10. Praises Kemar Roach for his bowling and adds that he has lost some pace but gained in terms of accuracy. Mentions that in the batting department, they need to form more partnerships and focus on spending time in the middle. Regarding the debutant Gudakesh Motie, Roddy sounds very happy with his performance and shares that the target they gave him was to keep the scoring rate under 3 and he feels that Motie will gain from this experience.

Bangladesh are on the brink of yet another loss in Test cricket in recent times. They started on the wrong foot and remained behind the 8-ball throughout this game. A little bit of spark was shown on Day 3, but that's too little to turn the tide in their favour. They would wish for wickets in a heap this morning to send shivers in the West Indian camp like last evening, and if that happens, we could have a dramatic finish to this Test.

Welcome back, dear readers! A formality of 35 runs left in this Test match, and we've gathered here to get done with it. West Indies have played some excellent cricket over the last three days and earned the right to be in this position. When the situation demanded last afternoon, they were ready to put the hard yard with the ball, and eventually, it reaped rich dividends. There was a shaky start to the chase, but West Indies recovered well and would look to avoid a similar situation this morning. Stay tuned for more...

Right then, three days of the first Test between West Indies and Bangladesh have gone by and they have provided ample excitement to cricket lovers. The hosts have bossed most of the match so far and are just 35 runs away from taking a 1-0 lead in the series. They should be able to do so early on Day 4 if nothing surprising happens. The play will begin at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT) but our build-up will begin much sooner. Do join us then, take care and goodbye!

Kyle Mayers comes up for a quick chat. Says that to make the batters play every ball is the main thing for him. Adds that he looks to utilize the conditions and stick to accurate areas. Mentions that Bangladesh had a difficult first day but the pitch has got better since then for batting. Feels that it's all about staying patient on this surface. Further says that he and Kemar Roach go a long way back, and he calls him his role model. He praises Roach for always putting his best foot forward and wishes him 300 Test wickets soon. Tells that during that stand between Shakib and Nurul, they just wanted to stay patient.

Bangladesh did show a lot of fight on Day 3, especially with the bat as twin fifties from Shakib Al Hasan and Nurul Hasan saw them wipe off the deficit and even got them in the lead when at one point it seemed the visitors would lose by an innings. With just 83 runs to defend though, it was Khaled Ahmed who was sensational with the new ball and he picked up three wickets in his first couple of overs to just plant a seed of doubt in the mind of the opposition. Unfortunately for him, other bowlers haven't been able to trouble the Windies batters much and Bangladesh are heading towards defeat.

After a bit of toil in the field, West Indies made full use of the second new ball and Kemar Roach was the standout performer for the hosts. His five-wicket haul saw Bangladesh getting bundled out in the final session and that kept the lead to 83 runs. West Indies would have hoped to come out and play positively but that wasn't the case as they were soon reduced to 9 for 3. Since then, John Campbell and Jermaine Blackwood have put on a steady stand of 40 runs and the home team is now inching towards taking a 1-0 lead in the Test series.

Day 3 is known as the moving day in Test cricket and it has moved along at a brisk pace. A lot of action happened throughout the day but as the day comes to a conclusion, it is West Indies who are just 35 runs away from victory and they still have 7 wickets in hand.
Slower through the air, full and around off, John Campbell defends it cautiously off the front foot. That will be Stumps on Day 3.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Arm ball, landing around leg and skidding on, Campbell defends it unconvincingly from the back foot.
Slightly short in length, just outside off, Blackwood goes on the back foot and whacks it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy and around off, Jermaine is forward as he blocks it to the leg side.
Full and flighted on off, Campbell knocks it down to long on for a run.
Fullish and around off, it's speared in, Campbell gets forward and defends it off the inner half to mid-wicket. The ball rolls in the gap and they cross. 37 needed more.
Aims for a yorker but it turns out to be a low full toss, around off, Jermaine drives it through cover-point for a run.
Digs it in short, around middle and leg, Jermaine jumps and tucks it in front of square leg for an easy two.
Back of a length, around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it down from the back foot.
On a length and around off, John taps it down to covers and steals a single.
Short in length and wide outside off, Campbell tries to cut but misses.
Loopy and full, around off, Blackwood presses forward and blocks it safely. West Indies are halfway there, 42 more needed.
Flighted arm ball around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it in front of his front pad.
Drags his length short around off, John pulls it unconvincingly to mid on for a run.
Closer to off, continues to be short, Campbell stays back to defend.
Shortish again, around off, John again plays it down from the back foot.
Slightly short and on off, John Campbell goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Shakib Al Hasan brings himself into the attack now.

FOUR Thick outside edge and runs to the boundary! Ebadot Hossain bowls it short, and gets extra bounce outside off stump. Takes Jermaine Blackwood by surprise as it takes a thick edge and runs past third slip for a boundary!
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, John beats the cover fielder this time and gets a single.
Short outside off once again, Works it towards the cover fielder.
Goes slightly fuller outside off stump. John Campbell tries to cut it but the ball stays low and beats him.
Goes around the wicket, but still bowls it short and wide of off stump, John Campbell does not connect and will feel he missed out on this one.

FOUR! Smashed! Ebadot Hossain bowls a loose delivery to start off. It is short and wide and gives John Campbell all the time in the world to give himself room and hammer it between cover and long off for a boundary! 48 more runs needed now.
Ebadot Hossain to bowl for the first time in the second innings.
On middle and leg, flicked away leg side. End of a maiden over from Mehidy Hasan.
Nicely flighted, drifting into middle. Blackwood works it towards wide mid on.
Around off, pushed away tentatively towards cover.
On middle, this is turned towards mid-wicket.
A bit of grip and extra bounce this time. On a length, around off. this one turns in a bit as Blackwood gets an inside edge back onto the pads.
Tossed up delivery, on off. Blackwood pushes it towards mid on.
Full once again outside off. John Campbell plays it towards mid off.

FOUR! West Indies are getting a move on now! Half volley outside off stump. John Campbell gets forward confidently, strokes it with the open face of his bat towards point for a boundary! 52 more runs needed!
Full this time outside off, John Campbell leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on middle, Jermaine Blackwood works it wide of mid on for a single.
Khaled Ahmed bowls this short outside off, Jermaine Blackwood tries to cut it but the ball stays low and he mistimes it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on middle. Defended towards mid off.

FOUR! Up and over! This is flighted outside off, John Campbell deliberately goes aerial and lofts it over wide mid off. The fielder from the cover fence tries his best and puts in the dive but can't stop the boundary.  An expensive first over from Mehidy Hasan, 10 runs coming off it.
On a shorter length and around middle. Blackwood works it off the back foot and in front of mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely floated up, around off. Blackwood defends it out towards cover-point.
Around the pads, flicked away towards square leg for an easy single.
Good running. Flatter and angled into middle. John Campbell backs away and works it into the vacant area around wide mid on. They do come back for the second with ease.
Starts off with a fullish delivery on the pads, John Campbell tickles it around the corner and picks up a couple of runs.
A first change in the bowling as Mehidy Hasan comes into the attack.
Good-length delivery on off stump, attacking the pads. Jermaine Blackwood defends to down the pitch.
Pulls his length back once again on off stump. Jermaine Blackwood gets on top of it and punches it to mid off.

Full and swinging into the pads. John Campbell tries to flick it and falls all over it. Thumps into the pad and Bangladesh players appeal. The umpire reckons its going down leg stump Shakib Al Hasan does not review. The batters cross for a leg bye as well.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off stump. John Campbell strokes it to mid off.
Slightly back of a length on off stump. Jermaine Blackwood gets up and punches it towards cover. A misfield allows Jermaine Blackwood to get across for a single.
Bowls this full angling into the pads, Jermaine Blackwood knocks it towards mid on.
Goes around the wicket for the final delivery and bowls it full and straight. Blackwood clips it to the man at square leg and picks up a single.
This is pitched up on the fourth stump line, Blackwood defends it out off the front foot.
Full and outside off, going across the right-hander. Blackwood lets it through to the keeper.
Slower in pace, angling across the batter. Blackwood punches it out towards mid off.
Pitched up this time, around off. Jermaine Blackwood gets a good stride forward and solidly defends it out.
Fuller in length and angled across the off stump. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Good-length delivery on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full and outside off stump. Jermaine Blackwood lets this one go.
Khaled Ahmed bowls full once again, angling into the pads. Jermaine Blackwood works it to square leg.
Full and on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Middle stump line on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood knocks it towards mid-wicket. Tamim Iqbal collects it and has a shy at the bowlers end.
FOUR! Jermaine Blackwood glances this fine! Khaled Ahmed misses his line and bowls this down leg stump on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood does not miss out as he gets a boundary to fine leg.
Off-cutter this time from Mustafizur Rahman. On a good length, angling into the body. Campbell looks to defend but misses the ball and gets hit on the body. Maiden!

Ooh, the ball just took off there! Mustafizur Rahman bends his back and bowls it on a hard length outside off. John Campbell looks to cut it away but the ball shoots up sharply off the surface and goes through to the keeper.
Nice change up from Mustafizur Rahman as he takes all the pace off the ball and bowls it full and wide. Campbell is beaten all ends up.
On a nagging length, angled into middle. The ball straightens a bit and John Campbell just about manages to get his bat in front of the pad to make the block.
Slightly fuller and on off, Campbell pushes it back towards the bowler.
Right on the money! Around the top of off, Campbell keeps it out.
Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot. End of yet another successful over from Khaled Ahmed.
Jermaine Blackwood is the new man in.

OUT! Cleaned up! Khaled Ahmed is spitting fire out there and down goes the third wicket for West Indies. This is delivered on a good length and around off. The ball jags back in a long way and stays a bit low as well, skidding through. Nkrumah Bonner is a bit late on the defensive shot and ends up getting beaten for pace. The ball knocks the off stump out of the ground and Khaled is running away in celebration. 75 runs needed now with 7 wickets in hand.
Commentary.Howout: b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: On off and angling in, Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.

A huge appeal for caught behind and the keeper seems certain but it is turned down. On a good length, around off and shaping away. Nkrumah Bonner looks to play at it away from his body but gets beaten past the outside edge. The Bangladesh players all go up in unison but the umpire remains unmoved. Shakib Al Hasan does review it but UltraEdge shows that there's a clear gap between bat and ball. NOT OUT!

John Campbell looks for two but is sent back by his partner. This is angled in from around off and once again, John Campbell is caught in two minds. Campbell opts to leave it late and the ball goes off the face of the bat towards deep backward point. The batters pick up a single.
On a good length and outside off. John Campbell looks to play at it but is beaten past the outside edge.

A stifled appeal for lbw but going down leg probably. Pitches it up this time and around leg stump. Nkrumah Bonner falls over a bit as he looks to flick it away. Bonner gets hit on the pads but and the ball rolls onto the leg side. The replay shows that the ball is pitching outside leg stump.
Slightly back of a length and slanted across the right-hander. Nkrumah Bonner watches it go past him and through to the keeper.
This is angled onto the pads, Campbell works it around the corner towards deep backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! John Campbell is off the mark with a boundary. A touch full and wide, Campbell goes on the front foot and drives it past point for the first boundary of the innings.
Length this time, close to the off pole. Campbell defends it out.
Pitched up, around off. John Campbell drives it stylishly and times it well but finds the fielder at covers.
Full and outside off, swinging away. Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it. Just two runs and a couple of wickets in the over for Khaled Ahmed.
Nkrumah Bonner is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A double strike from Khaled Ahmed in his very first over and all of a sudden the game is turned on its head. Real loose this though from Raymon Reifer. Khaled angles it in on a good length and around off. Reifer is caught in two minds but decides to leave it. Reifer is late and the ball bounces a bit extra taking the bottom part of the glove. Nurul Hasan makes no mistake behind the sticks and West Indies are two down inside the first two overs. 81 needed to win now.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Khaled Ahmed switches to around the wicket and bowls this one wide of the off stump. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter in length, on leg stump. Raymon Reifer tucks it off his hips and towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Around the top of off, Raymon Reifer stays inside the crease to watchfully keep it out.
Raymon Reifer is in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A very good catch from Nurul Hasan down to his left and Khaled Ahmed strikes on the very first ball. Khaled starts off with a length ball that is angled down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to tickle it fine but gets a faint edge on it. Nurul is quick to move across to his left and takes a stunning catch. Brathwaite walks back early after a soft dismissal and Bangladesh are all pumped up.
Commentary.Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Khaled Ahmed to bowl from the opposite end.
Mustafizur Rahman angles this one into the left-hander, close to the off stump. John Campbell punches it off the front foot towards cover.
Full and well outside off, swinging away. John Campbell just shadow-drives inside the line of the ball.
A touch shorter now, around off. Campbell hangs back and fabs it down towards fourth slip.
Lovely away shape on the ball but just a bit too wide to make the batter play at it. This is on a length and outside off, zipping through to the keeper.
This is fuller and outside off, shaping away. John Campbell lets it through to the keeper.

Off the mark straightaway! Mustafizur Rahman starts off with a fullish delivery on off and shaping it back into the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite plays at it with soft hands and nudges it past the point region for a single. West Indies are underway.
